The final Ansei Ward has been tracked to the Motalion Necropolis. I must help Prince Azah recover the Ward and put an end to the Withered Hand's plot.

I recovered all three Ansei Wards and defeated the heirs of Suturah. The Withered Hand is broken. Their campaign of terror has ended. All that remains is to restore the Ansei Wards to safekeeping in Sentinel.
While <<1>> was recovering, he asked for my help freeing the other captives and placing ingredients for a cure in the <<2>>.
The bustling city of Daggerfall holds many mysteries. It appears that I stumbled right into one of them.

The Red Rooks attacked a caravan and escaped to a noble's house on the outskirts of Daggerfall, where they've taken hostages. Captain Farlivere of the Daggerfall Guard has ordered her soldiers to surround the estate.
Red Rook bandits have ambushed several caravans heading north from Daggerfall. They've stolen food from them.
The nobles now have the wolf's woe plants. Unfortunately, the bandits set traps all around the estate. The nobles will never be able to slip out past those traps or the bandits.

The Red Rook leader, Tharkul, stole Lady Noellaume's jewelry box. She's grateful that her family is safe, but she would love to have her lockbox returned to her once she's safely away from the bandits.
Bloodthorn assassins plan to kill King Casimir. If the King dies, the entire Daggerfall Covenant could fall apart.
William Nurin needs a scroll delivered to a Redguard named Raham in Koeglin village to the southwest.
<<1>> asked me to track down <<2>> in <<3>> and assist him any way I can.
The forest itself seems to have turned against the village of Deleyn's Mill and the villagers are in danger. I should see if I can help.
Glutton, the prized pig that belongs to the Daggerfall swineherd Wickton, is missing. Wickton suspects pig thieves, or at least one particular pig thief.
<<1>> thinks that werewolves may be trying to infiltrate and take over Aldcroft, just as they overthrew Camlorn.
I encountered a road warden outside of Daggerfall's east gate. He informed me of the presence of a dangerous and organized bandit group called the Red Rooks.
A haggard forester in Daggerfall asked me to go to Deleyn's Mill, east out of the city, and help the people there.
The Beldama Wyrd want to use the roots of the Wyrd Tree to help the villagers get away. But the same corruption that caused all this trouble has sapped the roots of their power.
Someone's murdering Daggerfall's poor. A beggar named Matthew thinks he's going to be the next one to die. He asked me to find the killer before that happens.
The Duke told me that Gloria has a plan to learn more about Faolchu and how to defeat him. She wants me to capture a living werewolf for the ritual she needs to perform.
The town of Westtry is cursed, haunted by the spirits of its inhabitants and the raiders who slaughtered them. The spirit of Leon Milielle, Westtry's priest, asked me to lift the curse.

Leon made a pact with Molag Bal that placed a curse upon Westtry. The final twist was when Molag Bal turned Leon's wife and the captain of the guard, Rosalind, into a vengeful shade. She may hold the key to ending this curse.

<<1>> commands the Lion Guard in Aldcroft. She asked me to take a new recruit out on a patrol to teach him a few things about combat. She was also particularly insistent that I learn the history of the Lion Guard.
Bloodthorn cultists attacked a group of Camlorn refugees. They kidnapped the group's women and dragged them into the Fens.

I encountered a captive refugee of Camlorn in the bog. She claims to have been kidnapped by the Bloodthorn Cult and traded to the hags, who drain the captives of their youth and cast their corpses into the bog.
<<1>> has lost a number of people who are either fighters or workers. If they're still alive, they're in or around the harpy-infested hills of the Shrieking Scar.
<<1>> discovered that Reach magic has somehow corrupted the forest and silenced the elemental guardians.
The Mages Guild is studying the site of the Battle of Glenumbra Moors. It's said that Faolchu, the invader of Camlorn, was originally slain here. They hope to find out what killed him in the past.
Now that I've figured out who sabotaged the rain catchers, the supervisors at the field have asked me to ensure they are cleansed.

Imperial invaders ransacked the Temple of Satakalaam, killing the priests, defiling the temple, and stealing the relics. High Priest Zuladr has asked me to reclaim the relics so he can restore the temple.

Necromancers have attacked Satakalaam. Survivors linger in the city, while undead roam the streets looking for victims. The nobleman I talked to said that his sister, <<1>>, was last seen near the big door in the center of town.
<<1>> is in the formerly corrupted temple in <<2>>. He fears that necromancers of the Withered Hand may attempt to corrupt and raise his remains.
<<1>> told me about an old and powerful harpy, <<2>>, that defeated him in combat. I offered to slay the beast and return with its head, in exchange for a share of the bounty.
<<1>> is afraid to collect any more harpy feathers, but he desperately needs the income they'll provide.
<<1>> says he's on a mission to save Daggerfall from the dreaded harpy threat. He claims to be famous, but I've never heard of the man.
To stop the hags, I need to defeat the coven's leader, Mother Murk. Otherwise, other refugees will be in danger.

<<1>> told me a tale of heartbreak and sorcery. His wife refused the advances of an evil wizard and paid for it with her life. She now wanders the shore near here in eternal torment, bound for eternity to the wizard who killed her.
Master Gaerheart says I'm ready to become a journeyman forester. He wants me to craft a Journeyman's Ring to show what I've learned about my craft.
I found a dead Orc in the bog. He carried a broadsheet, as well as a handful of sharp crocodile teeth.
<<1>> was the sole survivor of the Bloodthorn cult's attack on the Aldcroft lighthouse. She asked me to retrieve her father's pipe from his cottage so she will have something to remember him by.
I am ready to become a journeyman smith. To do this I first must learn how to craft a Journeyman Ring.
The Lion Guard is fighting to contain the daedra that have overrun Aswala Stables.
Stablemaster <<1>> has asked me to enter the Aswala Springs Cave to seek out the source of the Daedric incursion.
<<1>> has asked me to help slay Daedra in Aswala Stables.

The necromancer <<1>> slaughtered the <<2>> city guard and raised them as zombies. The undead prevented the citizens of <<2>> from fleeing. <<1>> then cursed the town by summoning necromantic auras, ensuring a slow death for all who remained.

<<1>>, a member of the Ancestor Moths in Daggerfall city, has observed a man named <<2>> disturbing the temple grounds.nn<<1>> fears this man may be connected to the Cult of the Black Worm, a necromantic group which follows the villian Mannimarco.
The spirit of Alana Relin has led me to a crypt that will provide a doorway to the past. Now we'll finally learn how Faolchu was originally killed.

Alana and her soldiers were ambushed on their way to confront Faolchu. Now Alana has been taken captive and the remaining soldiers are too few to divide their attention. Moreover, I still need to figure out how Faolchu was killed in this time period.

The Bloodthorn cult is attempting to take control of the spirits of High Rock knights laid to rest at the Burial Mounds. They also seek to control the ancient kings buried there, and have stolen their regalia for some dark purpose.
I encountered an Ash'abah warrior at the Tears of the Dishonored.
Outraged that some of the worst criminals in history have been raised from the dead, the spirit of Magistrate Fazzar has returned from the grave to see justice done.
While exploring the ruins of Dresan Keep, I stumbled across a locked tower door. From within, I could hear muffled cries of distress. Someone's in trouble!
I am ready to become a journeyman runecrafter. To do this I first must learn how to craft a Journeyman Ring.
I am ready to become a journeyman outfitter. To do this I first must learn how to craft a Journeyman Ring.nnThen I have to show a completed ring to Outfitter Wickton.
I met a woman who's worried about her missing family.
<<1>> fears the <<2>> could still pose a serious danger if not handled properly. He suggested I seek the advice of a fellow Ancestor Moth, <<3>>, who studies the mysteries of the occult.
The dead lords and ladies of the mounds can't rest knowing the Bloodthorn cult has enthralled their servants.
The Beldama Wyrd asked for my help. The Wyrd rely on the elemental guardians for guidance and counsel, but the spirits have become mysteriously silent.

We must find where <<1>> is located. <<2>> has a Soul Gem that can impose a person's will on a spirit. If this gem is used on a Withered Hand cultist, the cultist's spirit can be forced to reveal Shiri's location.

A Moth Priestess in Aldcroft fears the Black Worm cult may be at work on the town's docks. There's a ship at anchor carrying a cargo of unconsecrated corpses. <<1>> has been denied access to the ship. He suspects necromancers are at work.
Angof Gravesinger has imprisoned the elemental guardians that the Beldama Wyrd rely on for protection and counsel. I agreed to help the Wyrd set the guardians free.
The city of Camlorn has fallen to Faolchu and his werewolf legion. The Lion Guard struggles to retake the city, but the odds are against them.

Kabrahla must stay behind in Lainlyn. She needs to follow up my banishing of the curse on the town with a blessing. For this reason, she will not be joining me at Motalion. Hopefully, she'll arrive later.
Kabrahla must stay behind in Lainlyn. She needs to follow up my banishing of the curse upon the town with a blessing. She won't be joining me at Motalion, but she'll be arriving later.

Kabrahla must stay behind in Lainlyn. She needs to follow up my banishing of the curse upon the town with a blessing. For this reason, she will not be joining me at Motalion. She'll be arriving later.

To hold back Angof's undead army, the Lion Guard built a redoubt on a hill outside Cath Bedraud. As they struggle to find a way to breech Angof's defenses, they have to fend off hordes of Bloodthorn cultists and zombie thralls.

Grand Warlord Zimmeron has authorized a bonus for any Pact soldier who slays 20 enemy combatants.

A stranger came to the Ash'abah camp at Morwha's Bounty last night and feasted with them. By morning, he was gone, and the Ash'abah's johad wells were poisoned. Already weakened, the tribe found itself beset by undead from the sands.
The town of Eagle's Brook has been overrun. It sounds like Red Rook bandits are involved.
Marimah has succumbed to the poison and lies dying. Zal at-Zazir is attending to him, but he says he needs ingredients before he can cleanse the destructive toxin.

The Bloodthorn cult took control of Eagle's Brook. They're using it as a staging area for their undead army. The necromancer Lord Velian is raising corpses as undead soldiers within a barricaded, warded hideout.
The Bloodthorn plan for an undead army has been slowed, but the spell binding the Red Rooks to Eagle's Brook is still a threat.

A detachment of Lion Guard soldiers was massacred by House Montclair forces at the <<1>> north of Oldgate. <<2>> needs help blessing the corpses strewn across the battlefield. This prevents them from rising as undead abominations.
I've become a novice in the Forester's guild. Guildmaster Gaerheart will be my teacher, based out of the lumber mill in Daggerfall.
I've become a novice in the Runecrafter's guild. Guildmaster Ashton will be my teacher, based out of the runehall in Daggerfall.
A Crown bride, Tiela, has been left at the altar because the Forebear groom, Casnar, hasn't shown up for the wedding. Both families are angry, and I've agreed to help settle the matter.

General Gautier believes his son Darien, the Captain of the Camlorn Guard is still alive inside the city. He hopes to use Darien's master key to unlock the Camlorn gates. Then the Lion Guard can surround Faolchu's werewolves and retake the city.
I've become a novice in the Smith's guild. Guildmaster gro-Izburg will be my teacher, based out of the forge in Daggerfall.

<<1>> told me that the Bloodthorn cultists have placed totems in huts around the Wyrd Tree. Those totems are spewing corruption magic all over this area. They must be removed before the Guardians can begin to cleanse the Wyrd Tree.
The elemental guardian asked me to head for the Wyrd Tree. I need to find Wyress Gwen and help save the Wyrd Tree.
The Mages Guild has researchers looking into the details surrounding the way Faolchu originally died. It happened at an ancient battle site called the Glenumbra Moors.
The Sentinel Guard is concerned about the rioting dock workers. <<1>> hopes to discover the source of their discord to resolve things peacefully before resorting to force.
<<1>> has noticed a suspicious man at the Sentinel Docks. He believes he's responsible for the rioting workers and sabotaged boats.
A Khajiit named Ildani was apparently caught trying to smuggle her wares into Sentinel. She's asked me to help her recover the confiscated goods.
An envoy of <<1>> told me that <<1>> has requested my presence at his royal palace.
I am now officially a member of the Ash'abah, and I am setting forth to destroy the Withered Hand. Talia suggested I visit Tu'whacca's Throne to see if the Withered Hand has been there.
Angof's Bloodthorn cultists threaten the Wyrd Tree. I should help the Beldama Wyrd save the tree.

I met Harald Winvale, a repentant Bloodthorn cultist who is being haunted by ancestral spirits for desecrating his family tombs. He asked me to help him demonstrate that he still honors and respects his ancestors.

I discovered a suspicious trapdoor in the cellar of the <<1>> Inn. I've decided I should investigate and discover what's beyond the door.
Gabrielle Benele, the Mages Guild scholar I found in the caves north of Cath Bedraud, wants me to find an artifact that can help the Lion Guard defeat Angof.
The wizard Gabrielle Benele asked me to help her recharge the Midnight Talisman. It could be a powerful weapon in the battle against Angof the Gravesinger.

The city of Evermore is in dire straits. King Eamond is dead and Reachmen are bearing down on the city from the north. Duke Renchant plans to hand the city over to Imperial control, but I have agreed to work with Queen Arzhela to stop him.
After we thwarted the Imperial plot in Evermore, Uela the crow paid me another visit to say we're enemies again now and that her Reachmen army is going to kill everyone in Evermore.
<<1>> said that the Wyrd Tree will recover, but another danger has appeared in the north.
<<1>> received a mortal wound in the fighting at Bangkorai Garrison. He has a plan to defeat the Imperials, and he's requested my help.
A Daggerfall noble named Lady Laurent seems to be some kind of treasure hunter. She's exploring the Tomb of Lost Kings to find something to add to her collection.

A contingent of Shornhelm Guard soldiers was on patrol when it was attacked by House Montclair troops. The Guard survivors have taken refuge in an old tower on Hinault Farm, where they continue to be under siege by Montclair's forces.
<<1>> is expecting aid from Wayrest. The threat of a Reachmen attack is looming over Evermore. She has yet to hear any news of its arrival.
In the battle for Bangkorai Garrison, too many soldiers were killed for all the bodies to be consecrated. <<1>> has asked for my help.
A large number of spirits are inside Pelin Temple. I was able to point out to <<1>> that she was dead and she was able to move on.nnI should try to help the others move on as well.
<<1>> has revealed that <<2>> and <<3>> are really trying to raise <<4>> as a revenant to aid in the fight against the Imperials.
The ruins of <<1>> are under a curse.
The ruins of <<1>> are under a curse. According to <<2>>, I am the legendary hero who will break it.
The ghost of <<1>> appeared to me at <<2>>. He said that the spirits haunting the ruins are cursed to live out their final moments again and again.
Harpies are abducting people from Daggerfall. <<1>> and her troops are there to rescue them, but her soldiers are losing ground, and they need my help.
Now that the rain catchers have been repaired, Sentinel needs to send more workers to the Rain Catcher Fields.
The spirits of four legendary Redguards stand around the central shrine atop HoonDing's Watch. Each poses a challenging choice based on a difficult decision they once had to make.

<<1>> fears Mannimarco's Worm Cult will continue to present ever greater dangers to the Order of the Ancestor Moth. She wishes to warn her fellow priests of this danger, starting with those in nearby <<2>>.
<<1>> and I found <<2>> dead in his house. Their children  Jowan, Marrec, and Mayla  and his wife, Melita, were missing.

Daedra attacked  <<1>> last night, driving the at-Aswala family and their stablehands from their beds. Now Stablemaster <<2>> plans to beseech his ancestors for help driving the beasts back into Oblivion.
Lion Guard soldiers have blocked the path into Camlorn. They're telling all travelers of recent troubles. Werewolves have overrun the town. I need to speak to the commanding forces.
This is a blank template for the Interact with IO, Collect Quest Item, and Use Quest Item conditions.
The Red Rooks have taken over the Crosswych Mines, turning the miners into slaves. Further, anyone who resists them are sent into the mines as prisoners.
While exploring, Lady Clarisse Laurent mistakenly opened a portal allowing Aldmeri Dominion soldiers to invade the ruins of Salas En. I've agreed to help her close the portal.
The risen dead and the Aldmeri Dominion forced <<1>> and her Saltwalker mercenary crew out of <<2>>. She was forced to abandon the ruins before she could find all the missing pieces to her amulet.
I discovered an Orc imprisoned in the dungeons below Salas En. He claims to have lived there for centuries, kept alive by Aldmeri enchantment. The stones of his prison glow with mysterious energies.
<<1>> knows the Ash'abah at <<2>> are in need of assistance. Because of his beliefs, he couldn't help them.
<<1>> is one of the masters of Anvil's Heart. <<2>> trains Redguards in martial philosophy. He also tutors students in the ways of the ancient masters, such as the Ansei.
I encountered an injured Lion Guard knight named Sir Malik Nasir in Merovec's Folly. He wants to stop the Bloodthorn cultists from desecrating the dead Lion Guard soldiers.
I encountered the spirit of Richard Dusant, who died searching for the hidden treasure of Dresan Keep. He wants me to finish his search for the Keep's ancient secrets.
I found a bloody talisman on the corpse of one of the risen dead. It was probably taken from one of the slain Ash'abah warriors.
Lady Laurent, a traveling archeologist, has "lost" her assistant, Stibbons. She is trying to recover him from her research site.
<<1>> has asked me to bring him any tablets I find in the ruins of <<2>>.
<<1>> asked me to free the gargoyles the Imperials caged.
I am providing to Runecrafter Arcole that I am qualified to become an expert runecrafter.nnI have to craft an Expert Ring and show it to him.
The spirit of Richard Dusant said I should take the Dresan Index to someone in the Mages Guild.
I am ready to become an expert forester. To do this I first must learn how to craft an Expert Ring.nnThen I have to show a completed ring to Forester Gelves.
I am ready to become an expert smith. To do this I first must learn how to craft an Expert's Ring.
I am ready to become an expert outfitter. To do this I first must learn how to craft a Expert's  Ring.nnThen I have to show a completed ring to Outfitter Susulma.
<<1>> near the entrance to the Sunken Road caverns told me that the Shining Scarabs give ration tokens to those living in the caves.
Recently, the Shining Scarabs have been acting strangely towards the residents of the Sunken Road.
target: Recently, the Shining Scarabs have been acting strangely towards the residents del Soleken Road.

source: I found an amulet along the Sunken Road with an inscription engraved on it: "To M. from A.  Love Eternally."
I returned from the past with the knowledge we need to defeat Faolchu. Fire weakens him and makes him vulnerable.
I encountered a Lion Guard runner at a camp near the Dwynnarth Ruins who asked me to visit the Redoubt.
The Sentinel Docks have been overrun with undead and the guards don't appear to be doing anything in response. I told Captain Marck I would try to find out what's going on.
<<1>> said the Withered Hand has taken his daughter, <<2>>, to use in a ritual. He fears she doesn't have long to live.
Soldiers from Evermore were defeated at Murcien's Hamlet by a Reachman attack.
I am ready to become an expert forester. To do this I first must learn how to craft an adept ring.nnThen I have to show a completed ring to Forester Gelves.
The Red Rook bandits have taken control of the town of Crosswych. Some of the townsfolk are trying to organize a resistance, but the bandits are determined to use the town as a base.
Sir Lanis and the Knights of the Dragon are ready to march into Cath Bedraud to deal with Angof, but the mist rising from Angof's vines creates a hazard they can't overcome.
target: Sir Lanis and the Knights del Drago are ready to march into Cath Bedraud to deal with Angof, but the mist rising from Angof's vines creates a hazard they can't overcome.

source: I am ready to become an adept outfitter. To do this I first must learn how to craft an Adept's  Ring.
Unusually clever wolves are attacking people in Cambray Pass.
I am providing to Runecrafter Arcole that I am qualified to become an adept runecrafter.nnI have to craft an Adept's Ring and show it to him.
I am ready to become an adept smith. To do this I first must learn how to craft an Adept's Ring.
<<1>> says the Crosswych resistance has gained enough momentum. It's time to deal with the Red Rooks' leader, <<2>> himself.
I've come upon <<1>>, a sun-baked wanderer. He inhabits a murky oasis near Tu'whacca's Throne. The wanderer seems to be speaking in fables regarding Sep's Hunger and a pearl.
Red Rook enforcers are extorting gold from the citizens of Crosswych. They claim it's to pay for the protection they're providing, but that's just an excuse.
<<1>>, the snake charmer, has lost his trained snake, <<2>>.
I've returned to the murky oasis near Tu'whacca's Throne. <<1>>, the sun-baked wanderer, is once again speaking in fables regarding Sep's Hunger and a pearl.

The Fighters Guild has declared their support for the nobility of Sentinel. They are now in open combat against the Withered Hand. The Hand's attack against the town of Lainlyn has proven particularly difficult for the Guild.
A Reachman known as <<1>> is the cause of turmoil in the <<2>>. To stop him, we must regain the favor of Hircine, a Daedric Prince the Wyrd revere.
The Daedric Prince Hircine told me the secret to defeating Brinarch. Once he is slain, the <<1>> will again be in the hands of the Wyrd.

In the sewers beneath Wayrest, I met a man named <<1>> who was ruined by a group of smugglers and now seeks bloody revenge. The Pellingare gang, as he names them, use the sewers as the headquarters for their smuggling operations.
Several Shining Scarabs recruits patrolling Sunken Road's lower cavern have not returned to the camp, and may be injured.
An old Redguard sitting in the desert is contemplating fate. He believes all of our actions are predetermined.
<<1>> wants more information on the state of the Imperial army. She asked me to lead <<2>> on a reconnaissance mission to the Bangkorai garrison south of the mustering camp.
This is a blank template for the Kill X quest condition.
I discovered the body of a dead <<1>> in the ruins of <<2>>. His hand held an old censer, still filled with incense.
The final battle against Angof begins now. I need to get inside and navigate the labyrinth of catacombs to find a safe place for Gabrielle and the soldiers to teleport into.

A group of smugglers known as the Pellingare gang is operating out of Wayrest sewers. The smugglers act with near impunity in the city. A corrupt investigator named Garron is helping the gang cover up their crimes by framing innocent citizens.
Reachmen have attacked Evermore Farms and are holding prisoners near the farms' center.
The ancient weapon of power, Bonerender, that has been hidden at Evermore Farms for years has gone missing.
Marge Themond is tending to wounded in the house near the windmill in Evermore Farms.
This is an escort quest, using Event Success, Event Fail and Go To Waypoint.
This quest will use the Talk to NPC, Interact with NPC and Give/Show Item conditions. You can use monster 16493 for these interactions.
A Redguard named Hadoon believes ones fate is not predetermined. He believes one can break from destiny but needs help proving his theory.

I've come across a friendly goblin in the ruins of a caravan near Bergama. He was aiding a group of Dunmer slavers, and his wagon train was hit by the Withering Hand. He now fears for his life, afraid the other goblin survivors will kill him.
I found a sealed reliquary within <<1>> and decided to open it. The spirit of a knight appeared before me.
Halelah had a terrible vision concerning the town of Satakalaam. She couldn't see its details, so she's travelling there to find out more.
<<1>> needs my help to consecrate the bones of <<2>>, a member of the now destroyed Dark Council that once plotted to take over <<3>>.
The Imperials have pressed captives into service working in the mines at Onsi's Breath. I have offered to aid in their rescue.
Reachmen entered an area in <<1>> known as <<2>>.
<<1>> plans to sacrifice <<2>> and several other villagers to Hircine. She's found a way to control werewolves, so the werewolves of Kerbol's Hollow are relying on me to stop her.
A detachment of Evermore soldiers is encamped outside <<1>>. They're in danger of being attacked by any Reachmen leaving <<1>>.
The Aldmeri Dominion has made an incursion into Glenumbra, securing the stronghold of <<1>>. Within the tower I met a Lion Guard scout.
<<1>> asked me to interrogate the prisoner we captured outside <<2>>. She hopes he can confirm our suspicions about the weakness of the Imperial forces occupying the fortress.
I've started on a task for a dead sorcerer. Through an arcane stone, the mage's spirit is passing me instructions. Instructions for revenge.
Darien discovered that we need three shard-keys to open the three locks that protect Angof's inner sanctum.
I've decided to help <<1>> find a lizard who can win in the local lizard races. Breeders specialize in providing varieties of racing reptiles.
Letiza and her fiance tried to retrieve a small cache of gems in an old abandoned mine but were turned back by a ghost and some other creatures.

I met a miner named Samsi at the Badwater mine. She tells me that the mine is collapsing and her partner is trapped inside. I told her I would go in and find her partner. If he's dead, she still needs his supply pack.
I found a badly-beaten Orc in the mines at Onsi's Breath. He has asked for help in assuring that the resistance fighters can escape without the Imperials giving chase.
I met a sad looking dog beside a path in the Alik'r Desert. She seems to want my help.
Some peasants from the surrounding area were taken by trolls from the <<1>>.
More and more Crosswych citizens are joining the resistance against the Red Rooks. Tamien Sellan has a plan to end the bandits' grip on the town once and for all.
I found an Imperial mine at Onsi's Breath. Redguard prisoners are working as forced labor in the area.
<<1>> has asked me to relieve the suffering of the risen dead at Motalion Necropolis. Shiri has raised many Redguard champions. Now she wishes to enrage them with burning soul energies.
<<1>> has worked for much of her life to create a text contining historical records of the Ra Gada. She is dying and laments that she will not see her life's work complete.
<<1>> and his team tracked a group of Reachmen to a tunnel. He won't take his team inside because of persistent legends about people disappearing in it.
A Lion Guard patrol on its way from Daggerfall to Wayrest was attacked by Daedric Cultists who referred to themselves as 'Supernal Dreamers'. The cultists kidnapped the guard captain.
The resistance has formed. We must now prepare to rout the Imperials at Onsi's Breath.
<<1>> just learned that he inherited an estate. Unfortunately, the estate appears to be haunted and is overrun by imps.
I met a wood elf named <<1>> in <<2>>. He claims he was a soldier with the Aldmeri until a practical joke fell flat with the troops.
Aldmeri Dominion forces have captured Farwatch Tower. They're using the tower to signal their fleet at sea.

I met <<1>>, an emissary of the Covenant who was sent to convince the Orcs of the Obsidian Scar to join the cause. Renault was attacked and seriously injured. He's asked for my help. If he can't get the Orcs, he wants their weapons.
Now that I've figured out who sabotaged the rain catchers, the supervisors at the field have asked me to ensure they are cleansed.
I encountered a hedge mage in the Obsidian Scar. She's lost her magical focus, and she needs it to cast spells. With it, she could free all of the imprisoned slaves.
I discovered a dead Ash'abah scout with a sealed letter.

I found <<1>> within the tunnels of <<2>>. She claims she and her husband, <<3>>, were kidnapped by the Oathbound, at the behest of an Orc named <<4>>. She managed to escape, but needs help rescuing her husband.
I found a dusty old scroll beside an ancient Ayleid coffer in the vault beneath Dresan Keep.
<<1>>, a scholar from Cyrodiil, asked me to search the Yokudan ruins at Ancestor's Landing for an ancient sword.
Bangkoari Garrison has been invaded by Imperial forces.
A Lion Guard scouting party, made up mostly of new recruits, has gone missing near Farwatch Tower.
I accepted a mission to scout Kingscrest Farm for the Pact.
I accepted a mission to scout Farragut Farm for the Pact.
I accepted a mission to scout Blue Road Farm for the Pact.
I accepted a mission to scout Drakelowe Farm for the Pact.
I accepted a mission to scout Alessia Farm for the Pact.
The ghost of <<1>> asked me to avenge the deaths of those who once guarded the <<2>>.
Bangkoari Garrison has been invaded by Imperials, but some of the garrison is now controlled by the Daggerfall Covenant.
I accepted a mission to scout Faregyl Mine for the Covenant.
<<1>> tells me his son, <<2>>, has gone missing somewhere in the oasis near Bergama.
I have been tasked with helping Sakim, a slightly-crazed old Redguard in the kindlepitch mine.
The Imperials occupy <<1>>. They've found a way to raise the Redguards' ancestors buried there. A spy named <<2>> infiltrated their camp. He now requires assistance.
<<1>> has become a bigger threat to <<2>> than the Imperials. I need to find a way to destroy him.

<<1>>, a member of the Ancestor Moths in Daggerfall city, has observed a man named <<2>> disturbing the temple grounds.nn<<1>> fears this man may be connected to the Cult of the Black Worm, a necromantic group which follows the villian Mannimarco.

<<1>>, a member of the Order of the Ancestor Moths, recently traveled to the ruins of Dresan Keep in central Glenumbra. After learning that the Worm Cult may also be at work in the ruins, I agreed to visit Dresan Keep and search for <<1>> there.
I have run into a strange man called <<1>> who was injured. He asked me to search Imperials for documents which are important.
Another Moth Priest appeared in <<1>>, warning of a Worm Cult stronghold hidden below the town of <<2>> in the north of Glenumbra.

<<1>> was able to cleanse the Cursed Panoply of its deathly spell, so that it can now be used as a weapon of great power. She has offered me this as a reward for the help I gave to the Moth Priests of Glenumbra.
The Breton Servant wants me to interact with the box  nearby.
<<1>> has asked me to help supply the Daggerfall Covenant by contributing goods to the war effort. He's instructed me to meet with the masters of the three trade guilds in Daggerfall.
Bloodfiends have overrun <<1>>. Most of the Lion Guard soldiers sent to investigate have been turned or slaughtered.
I found a note on a dead bloodfiend. It suggests a group of people in Moira's Hope attempted to wait for Lion Guard assistance.
<<1>> doesn't want to turn into a bloodfiend. He wants to preserve his soul.
<<1>> wants to ensure that his will reaches his sister.
A Red Rook messenger was captured near the Dwynnarth Ruins Lion Guard camp while he was on his way to a secret meeting between the Red Rooks and the Bloodthorn cult.

<<1>> has asked me to help defend the Daggerfall Covenant from outside threats by becoming a member of a crafting guild and contributing goods to the war effort. To get started he told me to meet Daggerfall's guild masters and learn about the guilds.
Captain Janeve has been bitten by bloodfiends. She followed Tainted-Heart to a cave near the refugee camp, but she didn't enter. She feared he'd take control of her mind.
One of the guards in the Fell's Run militia let me know about the civil unrest that's gripping the city. I should go talk to the Marshal to see if I can help.

Something has disrupted the otherwise peaceful town of Fell's Run. What used to be a harmonious community consisting of mostly Bretons and Orcs has become a place marked by internal strife bordering on outright violence.
<<1>> has asked my help in giving the dead of the Sanguine Barrows an honorable rest. He's burning the corpses discarded by the grave robbers, saving them from the scavengers in the area.
Beetles have burst into the Shining Scarabs' base deep in the Sunken Road. The beetles came in through a tunnel in the lower portion of the caves.
Imperials have entered the Shining Scarabs' base in the Sunken Road. They're stealing food from the upper storerooms.
While the mayor and constable deal with the Fellwatch in Fell's Run, I've been asked to deal with the Fellwatch mustering camp.
I have requested aid from the hero <<1>>  against <<2>>.
Fell's Run is unified once again. Mayor Orrard wants Northpoint to know Fell's Run is ready to support the city.

Sorcerer Vunal at the Brothers of Strife monument says he can teach me about the past. The Brothers were apparently once mortal leaders of the citizens of Stonefalls. The past may hold clues about these powerful creatures.
Before agreeing to help me against <<1>>, I must perform a task for <<2>>.
The Reachmen attacked <<1>> while looking for an ancient relic: the <<2>>.
I found a note that listed troop movements in Bangkorai. The note appears to be from <<1>> to an Imperial named Calatorius.
The Imperials are using fractures between the planes to raise sanctified dead to fight on their behalf.
Before <<1>> will commit herself to my cause, I need to prove myself worthy.

Ufa believes we can rally the citizens of <<1>> to rise up en masse if we make a suitably dramatic gesture. His plan is for <<2>> and myself to infiltrate the grounds of Govenor Seius' manor to instigate the rebellion.

A company of the Lion Guard was nearly destroyed by the goblins in Bonesnap Ruins. One of the survivors wants to honor his fallen brethren by recovering certain letters, written by the dead soldiers to their loved ones and carried on their person.
<<1>> asked me to join forces with his garrison. His commander is at a large camp north of the Bangkorai Pass.
Defeating the Dark Witnesses can only be accomplished by killing the Hagraven, Uela. Some of the Wyrd Sisters up near Jackdaw Cove have been searching for where Uela is hiding, but they need help.
<<1>> would like me to ask an officer at <<2>> to send help to <<3>>.
The Imperials fled Bangkorai Garrison, but they could still be a threat.
Corpses are crawling out of the ground at Pelin Graveyard and taking up arms. Prince Adrien was to be entombed here.
<<1>> asked me to travel to the <<2>> and inform them of Prince Adrien's transformation.
Evermore soldiers are trying to take <<1>> back from Imperial invaders. <<2>> asked for my help in clearing out the barracks and opening a way for troops to sneak into the garrison.
One of the wyresses saw two large ravens, most likely messengers of the Reachmen, heading due east from Halcyon Lake.
A man outside the <<1>> asked me to look for his son.
The Ebonheart Pact has landed forces at Northpoint. They're attacking the farmlands, burning and pillaging as they go.
Evermore's troops are engaged with the Imperials again in a pitched battle for <<1>>.
I encountered a hillman named Jonnedor in the Breagha-Fin caves. He said that Veraya's servants are raising the spirits of the hill giants and enslaving them.
<<1>> is worried about his missing father and brother.
<<1>> has asked me to help enact a ritual that should return his sons to their bodies.

House Dorell is planning a direct assault on the Doomcrag via the Shrouded Pass, a dangerous mountain path leading up to the peak. If I light the signal fires as I find my way, House Dorell's troops will be able to advance rapidly behind me.

House Dorell and House Tamrith have troops moving through Shrouded Pass, but they're having difficulty reinforcing the summit. <<1>> has discovered the remains of an Ayleid teleporter. She wants to rebuild it and use it to establish supply lines.
A hillman, Ionela, is worried about the mammoths the hillmen hold sacred. With only a few hillmen left to protect the mammoths, she fears the mountain tigers will overwhelm them and wipe them out.
The Ebonheart Pact has taken the Northpoint coastline, and they're preparing to assault the city. Any disruption to their camps or leadership will help weaken their attack.
A traitor among the people of <<1>> has allowed the Imperial army to overtake the city. <<2>> is leading a small resistance group.
Now that Dhakir's daughter is safe, he's free to join the resistance. <<1>> believes they must increase their numbers before they can retake <<2>>.
Elise Robic is sure that the Ebonheart Pact is not acting in Northpoint alone. She's asked for my help in uncovering a conspiracy.
Thomas Robic is very convinced that the handwriting was Baron Chirane's. It's time to confront him before its too late.
Molag Bal's plot endangers all life on Tamriel. I must put a stop to it.
<<1>> asked me to carry word of the strange events at the Hinault Farm to the Captain of the Watch in Shornhelm.
Chancellor Yvette has concerns that Baron Chirane may not have been working alone. There may be more conspirators in Northpoint.
Evermore soldiers are trying to take <<1>> back from Imperial invaders. <<2>> asked for my help clearing out the barracks. That should open a way for troops to sneak into the garrison.
I found a complex mechanism that looks very out of place in the <<1>> desert.nnNear the place I found it is a buried Dwemer ruin. It's very likely the object is part of some device within.
<<1>> asked me to notify a member of the Fighters Guild in <<2>> about Zunaida's death.
<<1>>, the new Viridian Sentinel, senses that Evermore's farmers are in danger.
<<1>> has asked me to deliver a message to <<2>> in the <<3>>. The ruins are located in the northwest of the Fallen Wastes.
The prisoner that <<1>> and I captured provided us with details about the Imperial army's condition at <<2>>. <<3>> is the leader of the assault there, and he needs this information.

King Fahara'jad has informed me of dire circumstances in Bangkorai. King Eamond is dead and the Reachmen are marching on the kingdom's capital of Evermore. He has asked me to go there and try to rally the city's defenses.
The Imperials used gargoyles in their attack on <<1>>. According to <<2>>, the gargoyles' behavior was unusual.
An Imperial army is moving toward <<1>>.
I met a man who had a wife, said he would keep her all his life. The one day he met a girl.
Imperial troops overwhelmed the soldiers at <<1>>. With their force divided, the defending soldiers can't spare anyone to tend the wounded on the far side.

I recovered an unusual piece of metal plating from one of the Imperials in <<1>>. A message attached to the object indicated it might be part of a larger map, and that the map could possibly lead to a long-buried Dwarven artifact.
Refugees entering Sunken Road from Hallin's Stand are reporting a number of problems.
Priestess Brela believes the tormented spirits of a Dark Elf army haunt Vivec's Antlers. They died in a great conflict with the Akaviri. She was captured while consecrating their bones.
I need to talk to the Fighters Guild in <<1>>, so they can send a healer who can tend to <<2>>.
Covenant troops are massing to the north of Fort Arand. They don't have the numbers for a frontal assault, but Fort Captain Hjolm believes they may be coordinating an attack with a second flank.

Captain Noris came to Vivec's Antlers to defend against an incursion by Alexandra Conele of the Covenant. Alexandra wants to retrieve an artifact known as the Coral Heart from Vivec's Antlers. The Pact is barely holding its ground.
Now that I've figured out who sabotaged the rain catchers, the supervisors at the field have asked me to ensure they are cleansed.
<<1>> asked me to help slow the Covenant's siege of Davon's Watch.
Covenant forces have scaled the walls of Davon's Watch. Now they're threatening to take the city from within its walls. Tanval's ritual may be our only hope to end the assault.
With the Covenant driven from Davon's Watch, <<1>> has asked me to return the living weapon known as Balreth to its cell.

The remnants of a broken siege lie outside Davon's Watch, broken by the appearance of an army of ghosts. A sergeant at the front, a Nord named Rhorlak, has asked me to decide how best to deal with the spirits.
Covenant troops have killed Captain Hjolm of Fort Arand, and they're threatening the safety of the recruits within the fort. Captain Llaari hatched a plan to respond to the threat.
A volcanic eruption and an infestation of shalks have devastated the town of Senie. The townsfolk are wounded, but distrust between Dark Elves and Argonians delay efforts to heal them.
Dark Elves have been disappearing along the road to Narsis, near the western mountains. An incursion of Orcs may be responsible. I offered a Dark Elf scout my assistance.
Even though they're dead, Ix-Utha's Argonian brethren still act as slaves to the risen Chimer. They've returned to serve their cruel spectral masters.
Furon is worried that his brother Giron has joined a "circle of mages." He wants my help to understand what they're doing.

<<1>> is grateful the dead have been put to rest. She wants to give of herself to restore the Starved Plain. She's proposed a sacrifice from herself and her students that will allow plants to grow again on the plain.
Naryu Virian has been given her trial to become a full member of the Morag Tong. In order to do so, she must fulfill a contract on her brother.

Before the threat of a Daggerfall attack, reinforcements from Fort Arand were scheduled to report to Senie. The troops will be departing soon. Captain Llaari wants me to check in with a Nord who should already be in the area, <<1)>>.
<<1>> lost most of his kwama in a mine collapse. He asked me to help round up the survivors and convince them to return home.

Tanval is traveling to Ebonheart to continue his fight against the Covenant. He wants me to travel on to Senie, which should have seen the Brother of Strife stride past. I should speak to someone in Senie about our victory in Stonefalls.
Svanhildr wants to break the Oathbound offensive once and for all.
I encountered a tormented Dark Elf spirit in the Orc camp at Malak's Maw. She asked for aid in easing her torment.
Senar Belvayn explained that a group of Ashlanders called the Vereansu attacked the village of Muth Gnaar. He wants me to enter the village and find his sisters.
Dolril Belvayn told me about the sacred relic, the Thumb of Saint Aralor. It's stored in the lower level of the temple. I promised to retrieve it.

Healer Ravel asked me to collect Saint Veloth medallions. As long as the monks are allowed to pray in peace, the medallions allow the power of the Tear of Saint Veloth to keep the Llodos plague in check on whoever wears one.
The signal tower near Senie warns of an ancient threat. I need to learn more. <<1>> suggested I speak to <<2>>. Apparently, he's a dead elder who rests in the necropolis of <<3>>.
The threat of the Llodos plague has allowed paranoia to run rampant. Many people in Narsis claim that friends and family members have vanished in the night.
I met a confused Nord named Norgred on the road outside of Quarantine Serk. He said he was escorting a witch. Apparently, she turned on him and stole a valuable axe. He's anxious to get it back.

A group called the Maulborn have set up a quarantine. They claim to have a cure for the Llodos Plague spreading through Deshaan. The afflicted go into the Serk, but some family members are worried that they haven't seen any progress as yet.
The Maulborn gathered the afflicted to intentionally accelerate the course of the plague. They're using a ritual to spread the plague and create an army of plague husks.
An Argonian named Onuja has come to Othrenis. He wants to know how to rebind the Brother of Strife. He's hoping to contact the spirit of Mavos Siloreth, an ancient Dunmer scribe buried in the area.

I awakened the spirit of an ancient Dark Elf scribe named Mavos Siloreth. Mavos's spirit can't remember how he bound Balreth in the original ceremony. To help me, he's going to perform a ritual and show me a vision of the past.

Bala, an Ashlander, is searching for her deceased lover, Eanen Varam. In life, he was part of House Dunmer, so their status kept them apart. They promised each other to unite in death, but now, she can't find his tomb.
I've learned all I can at Othrenis. Onuja says that Balreth is somewhere near Ash Mountain. <<1>> has led many Pact soldiers there with hopes of containing the Brother of Strife.

I met a confused Nord on the road outsisde of Quarantine Serk. He said he had been escorting a witch, but she turned on him when he spurned her advances and stole a valuable axe. He is anxious to get it back.
Forces of the Daggerfall Covenant are occupying the volcanic sulfur pools east of Heimlyn Keep. The Othrys family worked the site, but they've been run off their property.

<<1>> sent me into a deep vision with the help of an ancient ritual site. In this vision of the past, I should be able to interact with Balreth and Sadal. Then I can learn how the Brothers of Strife were born.
I met a man who wanted me to kill wolves.
Leel-Vata asked me to rescue the captured Argonian villagers from the Khajiiti pirates.
Dami Falvilo is an alchemist. She wants to acquire some of the Maulborn elixir so she can examine it. I think she plans to profit from the strange substance.
The lands of the mighty Hrogar are overrun with Goblins and spiders. The Nord has lost many men to the beasts, and he's under siege.
<<1>> has been taken captive by the Goblins, and Fafnyr was wounded in the fighting. The Nord warrior seeks revenge against the hated Goblins and their spider allies.
<<1>> has asked me to help him get revenge on the dreugh that killed his kinsmen.

I met a friendly House Hlaalu merchant named Raston Vendil. He's very eager to do business with the Mabrigash tribe, but he needs to garner the favor of their farseer before they'll consider trading with him.

The herd of guar at the sulfur pools stampeded during the Covenant attack. Now they're scattered. If I can calm them and fit them with the proper harnesses, the animals should return to the stable on their own.
The Covenant has seized Fort Virak. They're serving under the command of General Serien. The Pact's armyled by the Indorils, <<1>>, and Walks-in-Ashhas besieged the fort in an attempt to retake it.
I've infiltrated the ruins beneath Fort Virak. <<1>> asked me to help secure our foothold within the fort's main courtyard.
Fort Virak is ours. All that remains is to kill General Serien, the leader of the Covenant forces in Stonefalls.
<<1>> warned me that Tanval will likely try to release the second Brother of Strife from Tormented Spire. To ascend the spire I'll need to speak to the grandmaster of House Dres in Kragenmoor.

The Omen of Betrayal failed to manipulate General Godrun into attacking Wayrest, but has now trapped General Godrun within his dream. Abbot Durak has asked me to enter the dream and kill the Omen to save Godrun.
<<1>> told me the Mabrigash won't make a decision about <<2>> without first hearing from the Ghost Snake. I agreed to undertake a trial and see if the creature will speak to me.

A strong Covenant raiding force landed west of Ebonheart. The citizens are too busy with their own internal squabbles to unite against invaders. <<1>> fears the town may fall to Alexandra Conele's forces.
<<1>> asked me to search for a necklace that he dropped when he fled from the invading beetles. The necklace belonged to his wife who died recently.
After learning much from <<1>> at the Brothers of Strife, he told me I was needed at Vivec's Antlers.
Heimlyn Keep is under a terrible curse. A group of Covenant soldiers attacked, thinking they were assaulting a military target. Instead they loosed an ancient magic hidden beneath in the vaults.
I've helped the survivors at Heimlyn Keep. Now I need to end the curse. Its mystical corruption emanates from a Telvanni reliquary.
Merarii Telvanni is worried that Tanval may still be a threat. He was last seen heading toward the city of Kragenmoor at the base of Tormented Spire.

<<1>> fears for the survival of the Hist Tree the Argonians transplated from Black Marsh to Ebonheart. He thinks the Dark Elves of House Dres poisoned it, so he wants to fertilize it to encourage its growth.

A frightened soldier on the road told me about a slave revolt at Sathram Plantation. Ulov Stormwall led troops to the plantation, intending to suppress the revolt. Mysterious circumstances induced him to turn his blade on his own troops.
Ra'shadda, the Khajiiti shaman who summoned the monster, didn't leave the plantation. Ruvali speculates that he wanted to stay behind to watch the monster tear them apart.
I found a note on a dead Khajiit with plans for the riot. Apparently, the riot started with fires, followed by the freeing of prisoners.
A Nord named Hod lies dying just off the road out of Sathram Plantation. He asked me to deliver his father's shield to his brother in Iliath Temple. That lies to the east.
An extremely angry Argonian named Azeenus has asked me to seek vengeance against the Khajiiti pirates in his name.
Farseer Bodani has placed the fate of Raston Vendil in my hands. I agreed to undertake a trial and see if the Ghost Snake will counsel me on this matter.
Minister Ralden and Giron are missing. Advisor Varon believes that Giron is working with the Maulborn and has abducted Ralden.
Guard Rila wants me to slow down a group of agitated citizens to keep them from getting killed. She asked me to disrupt their meeting by using something they fear. I need rats.
A worker in Deepcrag Den, a kwama mine, told me the mine they were working had been filled with noxious fumes. The miners fell ill and it enraged the normally benign Kwama inhabitants.
I met <<1>> within Deepcrag Den. He was injured trying to get some scribs to a safe chamber.
Noxious fumes have leaked into Deepcrag Den, a kwama mine. The workers fell ill and the normally docile kwama became enraged.
Orona, one of the Deepcrag miners, mentioned that killing the kwama and letting them rot is a waste. She'd much rather harvest their cuttle, which apparently has a lot of profitable uses.
I agreed to help Madras rescue the missing villagers. However, I need to prove myself to him before he'll tell me where they're being held.
I shared everything I learned with Councilor Ralden. He plans to seal Narsis so that no one can enter or leave. I've been granted an exception while I work for the councilor.

Councilor Ralden and Giron are missing, along with many villagers. Varon Davel believes Giron is working with the Maulborn. Apparently, Giron abducted Ralden. I need to find them before it's too late.

I came across the wreckage of a trade caravan on the road between Mournhold and Narsis. Attacks on caravans don't usually occur this close to Mournhold, and the presence of a Dwarven construct makes this incident even more unusual.
The Covenant landed west of Ebonheart, but a band of Nord sawyers have refused to join the general defense. They sneeringly refer to the town's Dark Elves as "fancy lads."
House Dres raiders and Dwarven constructs attacked a caravan carrying valuable cargo. The House Hlaalu noble who sponsored this caravan will want it back.
A Mabrigash egg tender named Nerani explained that the snakes in the vale are restless. Their agitation hinders her work.
General Gavryn Redoran is acting erratically and completely out of character. Something has changed. I get the impression that Tal'Deic Fortress is in some kind of trouble.

The Dunmer of Ebonheart have turned to <<1>> for comfort in the face of an expected assault by Covenant forces. Disciple Sildras, however, believes the Tribunal has rejected the town. His gloom is affecting the citizens' morale.
I have mastered the basic apprentice recipes. Now <<1>>  is testing me to see if I can become an Apprentice Smith.
At the urging of a Pact recruiter, <<1>> is teaching me the basics of smithing.

Rogue Dark Elves flaunting the Pact are enslaving Argonians at a mine near Ash Mountain. A powerful Daedra rebelled against the mine's master. Then the Daedra took most of the people at the mine into Oblivion.
The Covenant has taken Fort Virak, a vital strategic chokepoint.

I met a strange little man who requested that I engage him in a game. He proposes that I acquire three items from some of his fellow carnival members. Once I acquire the items, he will take one from me and turn it into something amazing.
The Maulborn have occupied the Obsidian Gorge, the pass to Mournhold. House Hlaalu guards have cordoned off the area to keep anyone else from walking into a trap.
Shadowfen's Vicecanons are concerned about the Dominion running supply lines for their troops through Alten Corimont.
<<1>> wants to get rid of <<2>>, the Khajiit in Alten Corimont. Since the Khajiit is running Dominion supply lines, her sudden demise would benefit both <<1>> and the rest of Shadowfen.
<<1>> has a plan to steal treasure from Dominion troops before they find out what happened to <<2>>, their contact in <<3>>.
I found a map near the Aldmeri treasure ship outside <<1>>. With the help of my new pirate contacts, I should be able to find the treasure it leads to.

Due to archaic rules, <<1>> of the Aldmeri Dominion is allowed to undergo sacred Argonian trials at Hissmir. Success will allow him to commune with the Hist. To determine his true plans, I must pass the trials myself.
I completed the Trials of the Burnished Scales at Hissmir, which allows me to commune with the Hist. Doing so will give me insight why Captain Henaamo, a Dominion soldier, would undertake the trials.
Someone stole several relics from a cart in Hissmir. I offered to help <<1>> find the culprit.
A group of pilgrims failed to arrive in Hissmir as scheduled. <<1>> fears something has happened to them.
When I touched a sword, I got an image in my mind of a slaughtered goat. This is not a nice sword, but my path is clear.
I volunteered to enter the ruined crypts beneath the fort to look for the retainer, Durel Gilveni, and the mysterious others mentioned in the General's dispatch. The entrance is by the river.
It appears that soldiers known as Sentinels are terrorizing the fortress.
I met Kothringi from <<1>> who told me Worm Cult necromancers plague their village.
The town of Stormhold is plagued with murders and abductions.
<<1>> wants me to look into the disappearance of <<2>>.
<<1>> says some mercenaries in Stormhold are stirring up trouble between the Dark Elves and Argonians.
<<1>> is doing research on wamasu affinity for lightning, which they use for defense. He's asked for my help to test his theory before he approaches actual wamasu.
<<1>> suspects the Dominion skin-stealers are based out of <<2>>.
<<1>> believes he observed necromantic activity in Stillrise.
Elynisi's spirit has asked me to help her spirit re-enter her body.

Tanval Indoril has fled towards the Tormented Spire with the Coral Heart in hand. He wants to unleash Sadal, the Brother of Strife, from his imprisonment. Kragenmoor's <<1>> is the only one who can allow me access to the mountain.
I've discovered where Grandmaster Omin Dres' son is being held captive. The Vanguard is holding his son, Sen, in the tombs west of Kragenmoor.
A guar herder named <<1>> has lost control of his herd. Tanval's Vanguard drove them out of their pen, and Ral now fears for their safety.
The grandmaster of House Dres has given me a key that should see me past the wards at Tormented Spire. Now all that remains is to make my way there.
I've become a novice in the Runecrafter's guild. Guildmaster <<1>> will be my teacher, based out of the runehall in Davon's Watch.
<<1>>  is testing me, to see if I'm worthy to be an apprentice runecrafter.
I encountered a captive Dark Elf soldier named Saryvn in the ruins beneath Tal'Deic Fortress. He was captured by the Maulborn while he was avoiding his duties.

The monastery of Muth Gnaar was attacked by the Vereansu, a violent tribe of Ashlanders. The peaceful monks were caring for the afflicted using an ancient relic called the Tear of Saint Veloth when the Ashlanders attacked.
Text about finding Dolril and him asking for help.
Scout Kanat says that the rest of the scouting party is dead or afflicted, too far gone to be saved. He also says the Maulborn are protected from the Llodos plague by arcane wards.
I've become a novice in the Forester's guild. <<1>>  will be my teacher, based out of the Forester guildhall in Davon's Watch.
After returning the <<z:1>>, <<2>> made me the arbiter over the fate of <<3>>. Destroying the <<z:1>> will allow the villagers to die, but preserving it will trap them in their lifeless state.
The Argonian enclave of Lukiul Uxith lies in the path of the advancing Covenant army. <<1>> suspected that it's defenseless and suggested I check on them.
<<1>> wishes to make me an apprentice forester. His challenge for me is to craft him a shield.
A traveling merchant named <<1>> fell prey to Worm Cult necromancers camped below <<2>>. His guards were killed, and their souls are now trapped in animus geodes throughout the cultists' camp.
I've discovered an ancient Nord tomb in the depths of Darkwater Cave. Any number of treasures could be buried inside. But what else might be lurking there?
Master Silver-Gills says I'm ready to become a journeyman forester. He wants me to craft a Journeyman's Ring to show what I've learned about my craft.
Churasu has a way to turn the giant wasps into an army to use against the Khajiiti pirates. She needs my help to make an alchemical concoction.
I am ready to become a journeyman smith. To do this I first must learn how to craft a Journeyman Ring.
The Dominion is searching for a keystone in <<1>>. I need to find it before they do.
After Drillk's memory returned, he told me how to obtain the keystone. It's locked away in the Temple of Sul.
I've found a book about Ayleid 'Alasil pilasters' within the Temple of Sul. Beside it was a small Ayleid relic that may be able to awaken the pilasters.
I am ready to become a journeyman runecrafter. To do this I first must learn how to craft a Journeyman Ring.
I met an artificer who's trying to learn more about the mysterious rod that was used to control Dwarven constructs from Mzithumz.
I am ready to become an expert smith. To do this I first must learn how to craft an Expert's Ring.
<<1>> has asked me to help supply the Ebonheart Pact and contribute goods to the war effort. She has instructed me to meet with the heads of the three trade guilds in Davon's Watch.
<<1>> went to the <<2>>. He has yet to reply to <<3>>'s correspondence.
An Argonian and Khajiit planned a treasure expedition to <<1>>, but the Khajiit left early, probably to get to the treasure first.
The Mournhold Mages Guild has sent help to evacuate the wounded from Mzithumz.
I found a battered journal while walking the Coiled Path. A young woman named Risa did not survive this place. She lost her amulet fighting one of the snakes.
<<1>> welcomed a traveling High Elf to <<2>>, but she believes he has something to do with the wisps' recent aggression.
<<1>> is plagued by wisps. They're stealing away travelers at the gravesite. No one is sure what caused their sudden aggression.
To rid the area of her corrupting influence, <<1>> and I cleansed the ancient vessel. We need it capture the wispmother in <<2>>.
The Aldmeri Dominion has set up a staging area south of Hissmir in a fishing village called <<1>>.
Mournhold, the capital city of the Ebonheart Pact, appears orderly, even regimented. But the crowds seem more than a little nervous.

<<1>> led a force of Pact soldiers to Ash Mountain. They were following the Brother of Strife, Balreth. Using the information I learned from Mavos at Othrenis, we're going to imprison the Brother of Strife again.
I've defeated Ash Mountain's guardians. Now I must enter Ash Mountain's caldera, defeat Balreth, and imprison him again.
Scamps are boiling up out of the ground, no doubt excited by the freeing of Balreth. <<1>> asked for my help dealing with them. Collapsing the entrances to caves in <<2>> should do the job.
<<1>> told me of an assault force landing in the Ashlands west of Ebonheart. She's asked me to make for the land coral maze known as Vivec's Antlers.
I am ready to become an adept smith. To do this I first must learn how to craft an Adept's Ring.
I am providing to <<1>>  that I am qualified to become an expert runecrafter.nnI have to craft an Expert Ring and show it to him.
I am providing to <<1>>  that I am qualified to become an adept runecrafter.nnI have to craft an Adept's Ring and show it to her.
Geoffroi Stictal has been robbed of a precious crystal by cultist. It has been broken, but Stictal can reunite them if he has all the shards.
Lord Geoffroi Stictal wants the shards of his Crystal of Power back so his wizard can repair it.
<<1>> told me that his land's Fertility Crystal has been stolen. He needs it back before it can be misused by the Supernal Dreamers.
Lord Stictal had a unique power crystal that was stolen by Supernal Dreamers. They have shattered the crystal in order to use the pieces for daedric summoning ritual.
Supernal Dreamers stole a crystal from Geoffrey Stictal and broke it into multiple pieces. He wants me to retrieve the pieces from them.
I have been tasked by Lord <<1>> to recover shards of a crystal of power from the Supernal Dreamers who have stolen it.
Blessed by Veloth, I've come to Eidolon's Hollow to confront Magistrix Vox. It's time to end her threat once and for all.
The Daggerfall Covenant are attacking the Argonian village of Lukiul Uxith. Without support from the Ebonheart army, it won't survive long.
The Covenant attacked the Argonian town of Lukiul Uxith. The residents repelled the attack. They seem to be quite confident about their safety.
Pash-Riha hasn't returned to town yet. She's still hunting a Covenant lieutenant. Seven-Bellies is concerned for her safety. He believes she may be hunting southwest of the town.
I am ready to become an expert forester. To do this I first must learn how to craft an adept ring.nnThen I have to show a completed ring to<<1>>.
I am ready to become an adept forester. To do this I first must learn how to craft an adept ring.nnThen I have to show a completed ring to <<1>>.
I found Lord Geoffroi's son trapped in a cage.
Stephen Strictal is the prisoner of the Supernal Dreamers.
The son of Lord Strictal was taken captive by the Supernal dreamers.
The Supernal Dreamers imprisoned Steve Stictal.
I've helped the people of <<1>>. <<2>> suggested I move on to <<3>>, where <<4>> is working to push the Covenant invaders back into the sea.
Harvey was attempting to steal back his fathers shards when he was captured. He needs help escaping.
The Covenant has taken a resource site called the Sulfur Pools. A wounded laborer stumbled into Lukiul Uxith, barely alive.
Dominion soldiers have established a base below <<1>>.
I have been contracted to kill <<1>> by whatever means I choose.
I found a set of instructions on a Dominion soldier. It briefly outlines a plot to use portals to bring in more soldiers. They plan to sack Daggerfall without relying on transport by sea.
Although <<1>> rambled on, I gather a necromancer named <<2>> is raising skeletons in <<3>>.
I need to deliver a letter to Mudtree on behalf of the people of Stillrise.
I met a man who believes there is a monster in his closet.
I encountered a wounded Lion Guard member named <<1>> in the Bonesnap Ruins. He and his soldiers were sent to retrieve pieces of an artifact, but were ambushed.
A Daedric creature is loose in Bonesnap Ruins, and <<1>> has found a way to contain the creature by repairing a Welkynd Stone that's been damaged by invading Goblins.
The town of Stormhold is plagued with murders and abductions.
I met a pair of Argonians, former slaves. They want revenge upon Betina Volek, the last surviving descendant of the family that once owned them.
The grandmaster of House Dres wants revenge against the Vanguard troops outside Kragenmoor. He's commanded me to slay their leader.
<<1>> is struggling to understand humor. He heard a rumor about a sacred Dark Elf performance from the distant past.
The <<1>> is under threat from a Dominion force, yet the keeper of the grounds refuses aid from the Pact.
I found a strange device in the Dominion camps at <<1>>. The instructions for its use were signed "Alchemist <<2>>."
<<1>> now understands the Dominion's true threat to the hatching pools. We're doing something to stop it.
I've been sent to Zuuk, an abandoned Kothringi village, to locate <<1>>.
<<1>> knows his monks cannot defend <<2>> against a determined assault from the Kasgesh Ashlanders. He's asked me to appeal to the Tribunal for aid.
Something caused the creatures in Xal Ithix's swamps to become aggressive and attack the villagers.
Kotholl, a hired hand from the merchants' camp, was ordered to guard three specific chests with his life. He states it would be bad for the contents to fall into the hands of the Maulborn.
The Llodos plague has been unleashed and it's spreading through the gorge. Despite this, some Hlaalu guards are searching for the Maulborn alchemist.
The Dominion established a foothold in the small town of <<1>>. The Argonian Shadowscales intend to take back the town by force.
Factions of the Aldmeri Dominion have invaded <<1>>. The Shadowscales plan to avenge the village.
The diary of a dead Argonian mentions his impending marriage to another. Because of a Dominion invasion, it never came to pass.
<<1>> wants me to take word of our accomplishments to Hissmir.
<<1>> and <<2>> are the last survivors of their clutch.
The Argonians in Xal Ithix have been picking through trash piles. Now normally docile creatures from the swamp are attacking them.
The Dominion have landed an invasion force in the coastal village of <<1>>.
The renegade Ashlanders have broken through a storage tunnel beneath Iliath Temple, taking the monks and their defenders by surprise. If the attack can't be repelled, the monastery is sure to fall.
You're going on a journey to kill some dudes.
While investigating the murder of Magister Navisdyn for Almalexia, I uncovered clues that point toward a scion of House Dres.
Rigurt the Brash, leader of the Expedition for Nord Cultural Exchange, has asked for my assistance. I've agreed to trade a Nord book, clothes, and relic for similar Dark Elf items.
With Vox's wards shattered, the path to her lair is open. Aspera the Forgotten suggests this creates an opportunity to defeat Vox, but I'm not sure I can trust this strange projection.
A goat herder named <<1>> asked me to protect his flock of goats.
I found a note for Vicecanon Heita-Meen. It claims the Dominion's agents are stealing skins and using them as disguises to infiltrate Shadowfen.
The skin-stealers are operating from within the Daedric ruins at <<1>>. I need to stop them.
A Dremora named <<1>> is trapped within a Daedric device. She asked me to release her. Skin-stealers are using her power to fuel their magic.
<<1>> wants to find out more about <<A:2>>. Until the vicecanons understand its danger, they can't root out the Dominion in Shadowfen.
I found a Redguard mercenary named Ragara near the entrance to Zehtswater Cave. Her band was bitten and carried off by Lamias.
A large Maulborn force used the sewers to sneak into Mournhold. I need to find them before they can complete their nefarious plan.
The Shrine of Saint Veloth has been desecrated by Magistrix Vox. This Daedric attack has left the spirit of Veloth in a weakened state.

Acolyte Eldri collected Dremora hearts for Healer Dalen. He can turn the hearts into healing potions and wanted them to help the troops at Eidolon's Hollow. Unfortunately, Dalen departed before Eldri could give him the hearts.
Some terrible catastrophe has befallen Selfora, and now hostile spirits overrun the place.
I encountered a Sep priest named <<1>> in <<2>>. He asked me to help purify the wellspring and slay a vile creature named <<3>>, who is responsible for spreading sickness.
An Argonian outside <<1>> asked me to find his brother, <<2>>. He was in the nearby mine when Goblins overran it.
<<1>>, a miner in Mud Tree Village, asked me to recover some <<z:2>>s from the mine. He needs to raise money, so he can feed his family until the goblin infestation is dealt with.
While in the Goblin camp, I found a Nord corpse clutching a runestone that bears the name "Hodmar Iron-Kettle."
Tanval Indoril is inside the Tormented Spire working to unleash the Brother of Strife. Tanval's Vanguard holds the approach. If we don't stop Tanval, he'll unleash Sadal and destroy Stonefalls.
Mystery surrounds Forsaken Hamlet. An Argonian tree-minder lies murdered at the edge of her village.
The Dominion slaughtered the Argonians living in a small hamlet in Shadowfen. Only one remains alive to take his vengeance.
Elynisi has asked me to explore the temple overlooking Selfora.
The time to confront Vox has arrivedbut it seems that to defeat her, I need to die by her hammer. The Blessing of Veloth should protect me, but can I return from the dead?
The Shadowscales are undergoing a crisis of leadership. Perhaps I can help them resolve the matter.
The Shadowscales accept me among their ranks. They expect me to find the Shadowscale traitor who murdered their leader.
Though I uncovered the murder of their leader, some of the Shadowscales claim I'm a heretic who must be stopped. I need to convince them otherwise.
<<1>> is searching <<2>> for relics that could provide some sort of protection against the Dominion.

With Tanval's help, we've lowered the final ward guarding the prison of Sadal, the Brother of Strife. The mages who originally imprisoned Sadal linger on the Tormented Spire as spirits, angered by Tanval's ritual.
Priest Dilyne asked me to close the Daedric portals that Vox opened within the shrine. All kinds of vile creatures are emerging from these blasphemous wounds in the world.
Shadowfen's Vicecanon Hrondar sent Saervild Steel-Wind to Bogmother's ruins to collect Argonian relics.
I discovered a battered Dwarven construct that seems to have killed its Imperial caretaker. The Imperial's notes imply that they are searching for something within the Dwemer ruin at <<1>>.
Having saved Scybalum from Daedric corruption, I need to take the now-inert Namira's Hand to Loriasel for its final destruction.
Now that I have the holy vessel of water, the Selforan Spirit has tasked me to go out into town and rescue two people.
The vicecanons tracked an ancient keystone to <<1>>. This artifact would be a major boon to Pact forces in <<2>>. However, the prisoners seem unwilling to negotiate directly with the vicecanons.
The keystone is located within the White Rose Prison Dungeon. I've agreed to find it and use it to free the prisoners here.
<<1>>, a former prisoner of White Rose Prison, is dead, but her grieving spirit lingers on.
<<1>> believes his mother's remains lie in <<2>>, away from the swamp waters. Her spirit is unable to return to the Hist.
I've encountered a Covenant scout named <<1>> in <<2>>. She was captured by Imperials and has asked for my aid.
Njorlund Steel-Wind's mother Linnea went missing after the dreugh attacked them while they searched for Argonian relics.
The Forlorn One asked me to use the decanter of holy water to rescue two people trapped by the fires.
<<1>> of Ebonheart has lost her cat. She asked if I could help her find him.
While attempting to test a new spell, <<1>> transformed his brother, Dithis, into a female Goblin. The Goblin lass has been kidnapped by a local Goblin warlord named <<2>>.
<<1>> believes the spirit of a long-dead mage may know the secret to imprisoning Balreth again. An Argonian scout named <<2>> has already left for Othrenis.
The Guildmaster of the Fighters Guild wants me to perform a task for her.
Saervild Steel-Wind lured the dreugh to the ruins. His wife, Linnea, is still missing. She may be the key to uncovering what happened at Bogmother.
Sees-All-Colors has had Doshia's journal translated. From it she believes she may have discovered information relating to the mysterious Mortuum Vivicus.
Tenel Adren was hired to find someone to retrieve a rusty metal chest, outside Davon's Watch. The Daggerfall Covenant came across this box while in Stonefalls.
A shady character named <<1>> contacted me at Davon's Watch. He said we could both profit if I "procured" a rare and expensive bottle of wine for him.
<<1>> turned up again in Ebonheart looking to collaborate on another "business venture." He wants me to procure a bottle of <<2>> from an innkeeper.
Sibling explorers Raynor and Kireth Vanos are investigating the Dwarven ruins of Bthanual.
The wilderness of Stonefalls is filled with predators and hostile creatures. The citizens of the region would sleep better knowing the worst ones are dead.
This quest will allow you platform bots to complete a much neccesary quest for build verification purposes!
I encountered a Khajiit named <<1>> beneath Elden Root. She found that the Wood Orcs here are digging up ancient bones in order to give them to the Worm Cult.

I've accomplished great deeds with Tanval Indoril, <<1>>, and Walks-in-Ash. We've returned Tanval's Vanguard to the Ebonheart Pact, and convinced the spirits of Tormented Spire to open Sadal's prison.

I encountered an injured Bosmer within <<1>> named <<2>>. His sister, <<3>>, appears to have fallen in with the Worm Cult and has subverted the Darkfern Wood Orcs to aid in her excavation of ancient bones to give to the necromancers.
The vicecanons must be warned of Saervild's death. I need to tell them that Dominion skin-stealers are invading.
This is the Talking Quest.  The purpose of this quest is to talk to people and things, to  make sure the conversation system is still working.  Tally-ho!
This is a test of the new book tech.
A Dwarven device fills a chamber deep within the ruins of Bthanual. Kireth has repaired it. Beams of light now shine through prisms set around the room.
The Dark Brotherhood has asked me to kill <<1>>, a ship captain currently in port at Davon's Watch.
I've taken a contract to kill <<1>>.
I've taken a contract from <<1>> to kill <<2>>.
I temporarily freed the spirit of Benoit, a former student of Nerien'eth cursed to rise again and again. He has begged me to free the spirit of <<1>> from her daedric captors deep within the <<2>>.
The Ordinators are outnumbered. They asked me to reduce Vox's forces to help even things up a bit.
I ran into a Breton named <<1>> just inside the <<2>>. He wants me to find four treasures supposedly buried within and return them for a finder's fee.
A note on a dead Khajiit details plans for the riot. The riot appears to have started with fires, then the freeing of prisoners.
Guildmaster Sees-All-Colors has plans to make use of the crystal and tome we found in the depths of Mzeneldt.
I purchased a strange statue from an Ashlander merchant in the wilderness. It may be a religious fetish.
Researchers seeking ancient relics around the xanmeers found Renrijra pirates camped in the Argonian ruins they were planning to search.
The artifacts buried beneath Sunscale Strand are dangerous. <<1>> warns that we may have trouble with them. I need to be careful when searching the ruins.
I left the ancient Argonian ruins with a single Fang of Sithis. According to <<1>>, the Renrijra pirates are in an uproar. They may be feeling the effects of the other Fang in their midst.
<<1>> appears tired, and he's ready to return home to <<Ac:2>>.
Deshaan's Academy of Magic, Shad Astula, trains only the most promising mages to become leaders of the Ebonheart Pact. However, the Academy only accepts those who've received a special invitation.
I've taken a contract to publicly execute <<1>>.
I met a Dunmer named <<1>> in Apocrypha's Gate. He's a devotee of Hermaeus Mora. He and his fellows were attacked by rival cultists of Mehrunes Dagon, and their sanctum was put to the torch.
The Council of Province Generals has ordered an investigation into the death of the former Guildmaster, Jofnir Iceblade.
Within <<1>>, I found a devotee who managed to avoid the invaders. She's asked me to steal memories from the cultists of Mehrunes Dagon.
Dominion troops invaded <<1>>'s village, trapping her husband and the other villagers. Whatever the soldiers are doing in <<2>>, they must be stopped.
Jil wants a bucket, but we're glued to the floor.
I met a Dark Elf named Telbaril in a pocket of Evergloam known as Crow's Wood. He's trying to find his missing father, Rulantaril. He asked for my help.
Arch-Mage Valeyn believes I'm here to help protect the Academy against some unnamed threat. While he determines what this threat is, he asked me to help him with another matter.
Aamela Rethandus needs healing supplies to treat Selfora's wounded.
<<1>>'s husband <<2>> won't speak since his ordeal with the Dominion. I must find a way to heal him.
The Dark Brotherhood has given me a contract.
Arch-Mage Valeyn thinks his visions are somehow connected to the evil Magistrix Vox. Unfortunately, before he could learn more, something blocked his magic.
<<1>> tracked the Dominion's movement to <<2>>, where she hopes to end the Dominion invasion of Shadowfen.
<<1>> asked me to retreive <<A:2>> from <<3>>, the architect of the Dominion invasion in Shadowfen.
<<1>> is one of the few surviving prisoners from the Dominion's march into Loriasel.
After picking up an ancient sword in <<1>>, I learned an Ayleid knight's spirit haunts the ruins.
The Dark Brotherhood has asked me to kill a ship captian who is currently in port at Davon's Watch.
<<1>> asked me to find his son who hasn't returned to the village.
A talking crow claims to represent the Blackfeather Court. It says I must pay a toll to pass safely through the court's domain.
A high-ranking member of the Mages Guild, <<1>> wants me to perform a task for her.
