<<1>> informed me that <<2>> requires my presence in <<3>>. He believes all the problems we have encountered on <<4>> can be traced to the town on the north side of the island.
The Dominion took <<A:1>> to the Ayleid ruin of <<2>>. There they used its power to sever the Argonian connection with the Hist. As long as it remains in their possession, no Argonian eggs can hatch.
Thizzrini Arena is host to numerous arena games in a sprawling complex outside of Dune. To compete in the games, I must speak with the three Division Champions and earn the proper credentials.
I am competing in the Summoner Division of Thizzrini Arena. I need to work my way through the ranks in this division before I can challenge Tholbor, the Division Champion, in the main arena.
I am competing in the Sorcerer Division of Thizzrini Arena. I must fight through the ranks in order to fight Malarel, the Sorcerer Division Champion.
I am competing in the Swordmaster Division of Thizzrini Arena. I must rise through the ranks of contenders before I can battle Zara, the Swordmaster Division Champion.
I have defeated the champions of the three major divisions in Thizzrini Arena. Now I am ready to face Ishalga and become the Grand Champion of Thizzrini Arena.
The town of Arenthia has been occupied by a Colovian force. I've been tapped to help retake the city alongside a Khajiiti resistance force.
According to Centurion Gavo's confession, the Stonefire cult plans to summon a Dark Anchor within Arenthia.
I decided to ask Tzik'nith for help getting into the tower. Before she shows me the secret, however, she wants me to help her against the Wood Elves.
<<1>>, the slave dealer who runs <<2>>, sent his thugs to kill me and failed. His business partner, <<3>>, has grown tired of his slave-trading operation and wants me to eliminate him.
I've found a note from a Dwemer researcher's journal named Tharayya. She appears to have been searching for an ancient artifact referred to as the "Guardian's Eye."
Though Aranias was sent by the Veiled Heritance to kill him, the Wilderking believes she has actually come for another reason, and that our destinies are intertwined.
I found a notebook full of observations about the Ayleid wells around Cyrodiil. The book's owner may want it back.
Lady Laurent is displeased with her butler, Stibbons, for leading the Elves to Salas En. To get back in her good favor, he's asked me to help him by gathering Laurent's tools from among the ruins.
A suspicious woman asked me to relay a message to <<1>> in Bruma.
I found a set of robes in a bandit camp.
<<1>> is out in the wilds, looking for his son, Donus.
I found a note in a smuggler camp. A young Khajiit was captured and taken to <<1>> by the <<m:2>>.
Bowenas, the Treethane of Greenhill, is having trouble deciding what to do with Ezreba. The Khajiit helped the cultists to subvert the town, but she was forced to do so against her will.
I found a small silver flute in a crate. An inscription on the flute reads, "Halion of Chorrol." There might be a reward for the flute's return.
A spirit named <<1>> warned me of dark knowledge sealed in three forbidden tomes. She asked me to find all three and destroy them in a shrine on <<2>>.
I'm now partcipating in Lizard Racing, where I place bets on which lizard finishes the race first.
I'm now participating in Spikeball, a foot race where I can throw a Spikeball to stun opponents.
I'm now betting on the Troll Arena, where I place bets on which Troll wins the fight.
<<1>> at the <<2>> asked me to deliver a letter to his cousin Asvorn in <<3>>.
The chief of the Ash'abah and many of the tribe's warriors have been poisoned, most likely by the Withered Hand. I agreed to help Talia at-Marimah gather ingredients for an antidote.
There's a crisis at <<1>>. Something is wrong with their Great Tree, and the locals believe it has something to do with the tree's roots, which can be accessed from a cave below it.
Someone named Jena is being threatened. She apparently lives in Cheydinhal.
Bandits attacked a chapel just over the border from Reaper's March. A group of temple guards and their priestess tracked them to the ruins of Fort Sphinxmoth.
A young woman named Cardia has asked me to find her mother's ring. I should kill bandits and search them for the ring.
I met <<1>> fishing in the cold waters of northern Cyrodiil. She asked if I could bring some of her catch to her friend <<2>> in <<3>>.

I decided to ask Faraniel for help getting into the tower. Before she shows me the secret, however, she wants me to help her convince the Wood Elves to leave the forest and stop working for Molag Bal.
An Aldmeri Dominion fleet was shipwrecked here by a hurricane. I wasn't part of the wreck, but perhaps I can use the chaos as cover.
Sea Elves have entered Serpent's Grotto, and one of the Maormer mages has broken the seals that bound a massive sea serpent here for centuries.
I have a doctor's bag belonging to <<1>>, who may be in <<2>>.
Apphia Matia asked me to let Brielus Colus of Cheydinhal know that she is bearing his child.
On his deathbed, the chief of the Ash'abah says he has foreseen that I must join the tribe and defeat the Withered Hand. I must participate in an initiation ritual to become an Ash'abah.
The Eye of the Queen, Cariel, wants my help to uncover corruption in the little town of Pa'alat. She suspects a former Eye of the Queen has gone rogue.
I have been sent to the Moonlit Clearing to meet with a member of the lunar clergy. I'm supposed to find out if I am the Moon Hallowed.
The Shade of Prince Naemon has seized control of Hectahame where he is corrupting the Heart of the Valenwood. I must assist Queen Ayrenn and Indaenir in defeating him.
I found a letter from someone named Iocundus in <<1>>.
Awash in a sea of rats, Laughing Moons Plantation is in dire need of assistance. <<1>> asked me to help deal with the infestation.
A moon-sugar plantation suffered a terrible fire. The family in charge of the plantation needs a hand to recover from their tragedy.
The dead have risen at Tu'whacca's Throne. Throne Keeper Farvard insists we consult the king before taking any action. I have agreed to take word back to the palace in Sentinel.
<<1>> asked me to travel to <<2>> and look for her sister, <<3>>.
<<1>> has asked that I travel to <<2>> and inform his brother <<3>> that his wife is dead.
Clanmother Kazirra told me to travel to the city of Rawl'kha, to bring word of the Mane's change of heart.
The shoreline of Khenarthi's Roost is lined with the shattered hulls of Aldmeri Dominion sailing vessels. Equipment and personnel are scattered all along the beach.
A merchant in the Shrouded Vale reports seeing a village that has mysteriously and suddenly appeared in a nearby cave.

The army has been gathered and the time has come to take the battle to Molag Bal! But to reach the planar vortex at the heart of the Dark Lord's inner sanctum, we have to cross the well-defended Chasm.
The bulk of the Dominion fleet foundered on shoals in the storm, and no one has been able to get out there to look for survivors.
<<1>> directed me to <<2>> to rescue the members of his research team they had to leave behind.
I've entered Cyrodiil, eager to help the Dominion win the war.
I've reached the siege range. Zan advised me to try each weapon. I should also talk to Firamo and Miniel to learn more about the weapons.
Taralin says there is much more for me to learn about the war in Cyrodiil.
I found a note meant for <<1>>, who apparently lives in <<2>>. He might appreciate getting it.
<<1>> requested my presence once again. He's waiting for me at the bridge, most likely looking brooding. I should find out what he wants.
Lunar Priestess Kauzanabi-jo has indicated I should make for the temple of Moonmont. The Champions, the new candidates for the Mane, will join me there.
The priestess Kauzanabi-jo told me my next goal should be to help the people of Arenthia. Apparently Mane Akkhuz-ri is somewhere amid the Colovian invaders of the city.
I traveled to the city of Rawl'kha, where I'm to help the Lunar Champions begin their spiritual journey.
<<1>> in <<2>> is wanted by a pack of werewolves.
Vampires occupy the Orchard beyond the Chasm, somehow empowered by Molag Bal's Harvest Heart. The vampires need to be dealt with before our forces can push forward toward the planar vortex.
<<1>> asked me to deliver a message to his brother <<2>> in <<3>>.
Within Fort Sphinxmoth I encountered one of the chapel guards. She believes more of her companions were still alive elsewhere in the complex.
I saved Dune from the plots of Javad Tharn. Now I must aid the Lunar Champion as she walks the Two Moons Path, a mystical Khajiit ritual used to annoint a new Mane.
I have completed the first part of the Two Moons Path with the Lunar Champion. Now we must venture into the Den of Lorkhaj and complete the mystical journey.
Honorless criminals are left in the Tears of the Dishonored. Darius begged me to find the remains of his wife, Zariya, and consecrate them as he believes she was innocent.
I've arrived in Cyrodiil, ready to help the Pact win the war.
I've reached the siege range. Adalmor advised me to try each weapon. I should also talk to Looks-Forward and Lirtis to learn more about the weapons.
Galsi Mavani says I have more to learn about the conflict in Cyrodiil.
I've entered Cyrodiil, ready to help the Covenant win the war.
I've reached the siege range. Bugbesh told me to try each weapon. I should also talk to Marc and Jaleel to learn more about the weapons.
Aurorelle Varin says there is much more for me to learn about the war in Cyrodiil.

<<1>> told me of two threats on <<2>>. A temple experiencing a rash of disturbed undead lies on the east side of the island. A flagship dashed against the rocks lies on the west side. I need to decide who needs my help most.
I restored Vanus Galerion and disrupted activities at the Black Forge. Now we need to assault the Great Shackle and end the threat of the Planemeld once and for all.

I've been asked by a moon priestess named Felari to help with a project that could help firm up relations between the Khajiit and Wood Elves. They are working to return home relics and bones from ancient battle sites.
The Mages Guild has launched an expedition into Selene's Web to seek out and study an ancient forest spirit rumored to live here.

Queen Ayrenn must deal with the aftermath of her brother's betrayal and settle matters in Grahtwood. In the meantime, she asked me to travel to Marbruk, in Greenshade, and secure the Staff of Magnus from its vault.
This guy has a wolf problem.
I found the journal of Graccus, an Imperial who destroyed a Bosmer village to find a treasure buried below.
I discovered a Spinner named Melrethel imprisoned in the cellars of the Vile Manse. She claims to be from the Wood Elf village that Graccus razed and built his manor upon.
Vicereeve Pelidil and his Maormer allies have attacked and seized control of Seaside Sanctuary.
The Wood Elf brewing town of Willowgrove is trying to expand their beehives. They've hired help to clear the forest. This help appears to have suffered some difficulties.
They have no right to walk in this world again!
I found Minstrel Idria's lute abandoned in the Grotto of Depravity.
Pelidil's plans to lead the Maormer in attack against Valenwood have been exposed and Treethane Fariel suggests I go to Seaside Sanctuary to try to repel the Maormer invasion.
I found a pendant with the names <<1>> and <<2>> engraved upon it while exploring the Cave of Trophies.
I met a Dark Elf named Dralnas who claims that Dremora have taken his soul to feed to something he calls the Anguish Gem.
I found a hastily written note from Lady Laurent's servant, Stibbons. He was captured by Daedra after we arrived in Coldharbour and is being held in a nearby tower.
The mine called Kuna's Delve has been assaulted by a pack of bloodthirsty trolls.
Aranias and Andur were sent by the Veiled Heritance to kill the Wilderking. They are now forcing their way through Greenheart towards the Wilderking's throne.
A Breton shipbuilder named Jeromec Lemal has asked me to help him recover the warship designs from three ships under construction in the docks at Tava's Blessing.
I've arrived at Leki's Blade, a school of swordsmanship in the sands of Alik'r.
A woman named Arianas seeks to subvert or murder the Wilderking if he refuses to join the Veiled Heritance.
I met a Soul Shriven named Fatahala. She claims that this Manor of Revelry isn't what it appears to be. Furthermore, she wants me to help Stibbons, who she tells me is in mortal danger here.

The final assault to end the Planemeld is at hand. We need to fight our way through Molag Bal's defenses and reach the portal to the planar vortex. Only then can we end this threat and save our world.
The priestess Kauzanabi-jo told me my next goal should be to make for the temple in Rawl'kha. I need to aid the Lunar Champions in their journey.
The bandits at Sep's Spine have canceled hostilities for sake of the boss's daughter's wedding.
A courier came to me with an urgent request to go help Prince Azah fight in the small town of Tava's Blessing and to send the Scholar's apprentice, Shiri, back to Bergama.
I've elected to skip the introduction and jump right into the action.
Defeating the Shade saved stopped the undead army at Dread Vullain, but Naemon himself is still out there.
Abnur Tharn seeks an audience with me away from the Harborage. I should see what he wants.
Seaside Sanctuary is back in the control of the Aldmeri Dominion, but Vicereeve Pelidil has escaped aboard a Maormer vessel.
<<1>> is a town in Bangkorai fabled to have the power to cure any disease. <<2>> and his husband Draven seek whatever cure the village offers, though they don't know what the cost may be.
Mighty Mordra, an Orc woman, has invited me to join a group of adventurers called the Undaunted.
Dominion soldiers erected barricades around a tribe of Argonian refugees living in <<c:1>>. <<2>> needs help resolving the Argonians' situation.
The Maormer have revealed themselves as a threat to Khenarthi's Roost. <<1>> wishes to discuss plans to deal with any remaining traitors in Mistral.
I found an odd, glowing handaxe in a pack at the bottom of Gurzag's Mine. A note of sale indicated a Bosmer named Forthor sold it to the Orcs. He's part of the Marbruk Mages Guild.

Thonoras and his wife, Pariel, were captured and tortured by Wood Orcs. Pariel begged Hircine to save them, and Hircine "changed her." After helping her husband escape, Pariel disappeared into a cave beneath the Falinesti Spring Site.
I found a talking skull named <<1>> near <<Ac:2>>. He wants me to piece him together so he can help thwart Worm Cultists in the area.
King Dynar has devised a two-pronged attack to take control of the Reaver Citadel. It utilizes the old Fighters and Mages Guilds' halls located in this ancient Nirn city.
I ran into a very hung-over mage in Rawl'kha. He had too much to drink, lost several magical relics, and now fears he'll never gain an apprenticeship to Telenger the Artificer.
Tappo's journal details his victims. He kept a keepsake from each.
Whisper Grove has been turned to a City of Ash by the forces of Mehrunes Dagon. If I don't intervene, the remaining Bosmer will be slaughtered.
It appears a hunting band was overcome by a powerful wispmother, as their frozen forms are scattered about the mire.

Vanus Galerion of the Mages Guild has a plan to stop Molag Bal's incursion of Tamriel. It requires convincing the three alliances to join forces with the Mages Guild and Fighters Guild to assault Coldharbour.

I convinced the leaders of the three alliances to meet to discuss a plan to attack Molag Bal's realm of Coldharbour. The meeting takes place on the historic island of Stirk. Hopefully, the meeting will go smoothly.
Sorderion has charged me with apprehending Aldolin, a traitor to the Dominion who has been giving aid to the Ebonheart Pact.
<<1>>, an innkeeper in <<2>>, informed me of bandits who kidnapped his daughter <<3>>. He asked me to bring her home safely.

A small group of Wood Elves entered the Falinesti Spring Site, which has been taken over by Wood Orcs. When they petitioned the Wood Orcs to leave, they were taken prisoner. Egannor managed to escape, but his friends are still in the camp.
A group of Pact scouts was ambushed by the Lion Guard hidden in the mountains. Three scouts were captured: Hald, Hilka, and Fjor. I should free as many as possible.
The Vinedusks are spread thin and need my assistance.
A stone being named Sumiril carries a book that contains a story about how he came to be.
I met a Khajiit called Cold-Eyes who is looking to collect a debt. He'll give me a cut if I help him.
A Khajiit trader was tricked by an Altmer merchant captain who gave her low quality fabric in place of the rare silks she traded for.
A Bosmer scout claims her band was ambushed by Argoninan invaders. She managed to get away in the scuffle, but her allies are now captives of the Argonians.
A shady character told me I was needed at the city of Arenthia. This Orthoron said someone of my prowess would come in handy.
A strange priest at an old Khajiiti ruin told me that my path is laid out before him. He suggests I go to the city of Rawl'kha to learn more.
A mysterious Khajiit named Hunal spoke to me outside of the city of Dune. He told me some important task awaits me at the temple known as Moonmont.
This tower is a lightless oubliette, a prison of darkness that binds King Laloriaran Dynar, the last Ayleid King.
Indaenir and I cured the blight in Verrant Morass, but the corruption in the trees spreads across the region.
I found a journal that belonged to a monk of the Lunar faith named Yenadar. The journal mentions that he has a sister named Kala in S'ren-ja. I should return the journal to her.
I agreed to gather Red Mountain Ash for <<1>>, so she can make Nirnroot wine.
I agreed to gather Red Mountain Ash for <<1>>, so he can make Nirnroot wine.
I agreed to gather Red Mountain Ash for <<1>>, so he can make Nirnroot wine.
I was lead to an old instrument in the ruins of Thibaut's Cairn by a spectral woman. The recoder was engraved with "Valencia Nasica, the Exalted Bard of Dune."
Master Pellingare, a Wayrest nobleman, has gone missing. His guards, Yahyif and Gedric, have come to the sewers looking for him after he was last seen heading into the undercity tunnels.
I discovered the body of one of the Fighters Guild soldiers in Mal Sorra's Tomb. She started writing a note to her cousin, Grundskar, another soldier.
Nature itself has turned against the Bosmer village of Karthdar and its citizens are desperate to restore peace.
A villager from Tava's Blessing asked that I seek out a Thronekeeper named Luala al-Tava.
Scout Yanul says Prince Azah has his soldiers searching the desert for the Withered Hand.
After defeating the Maormer assault on Khenarthi's Roost, Razum-dar has asked me to report to <<1>> in the Auridon city of Vulkhel Guard.
I've been given a letter to deliver to Queen Ayrenn to bring her up to speed on the events that have occurred and inform her of our victory over Vicereeve Pelidil.
Gasteau Chamrond knows how to escape the structure I've fallen into. He'll help me get out if I lend him my strength.
A Bosmer named Adamir, and his associate Timiwe, are attempting to animate an assemblage of rodent parts.
Ledronor, a member of a hunting order called the Hounds, asked for my help in hunting a troll.
Radreth, a new member of the hunting company the Hounds, asked for my help in hunting a giant wasp.
The village of Shrouded Hollow fades back and forth from the realm of the forest.  Wood Orcs have taken their land in their absence and the villagers must fade back before the Orcs massacre them.
The Prophet contacted me through a magical projection. He asked me to seek out a place called the Harborage, where he has taken refuge. I should go to him and ensure that he is safe.
I've been summoned back to the Harborage in preparation for our battle against Molag Bal.
I've discovered an order of hunters called Brackenleaf's Briars. They protect a tree they say was planted by Y'ffre at the creation of the world.

While exploring the Tribulation Crypt, I encountered a ghost that beckoned me deeper into the tomb. The ghost led me to an ancient sword engraved with the following message: "Marcelle Stenric of Shornhelm.
Varen Aquilarios and Abnur Tharn have found the location of Sai Sahan within the Halls of Torment. I need to venture into these halls and save the final, missing companion.
Varen Aquilarios asked me to accompany Sai Sahan on a trip back to his ancestral home. An old friend, Kasura, may have knowledge of how to sneak into Sancre Tor.
A Bosmer named Maruin said that Aranias plans to harm the Wilderking. She is currently inside a story the Bosmer storyteller is telling.

While exploring Hildune's Secret Refuge, I found a journal written by Nadafa. It tells the story of how she was seduced by a vampire. The journal mentions that her husband, Giran, works in Northpoint at the cemetery and lives in the fishing village.

I met a Mages Guild novice named Anenya just inside the Erokii Ruins. She was sent here on an assignment to recover a relic called the Tear of Anurraame, but she can't carry it out. I agreed to recover the relic and bring it back to Shornhelm.
The Rain Catcher Fields, a sandy expanse of johads gathering water in large pools, has recently been overrun by beetles from the desert.
Explorers from the Mages Guild awoke an ancient threat at <<Ac:1>>. Undead creatures have slain or captured many within their expedition.
Undead soldiers have been haunting Traitor's Tor ever since the end of Ranser's War, but no one's ever been able to find out why.
I found a strange sapling that spoke to me, confused about its own ability to think and feel. It has vague memories of walking and a nearby cave. I agreed to help the sapling get some answers.

The combined forces of House Tamrith, House Dorell, and the Ravenwatch have gathered at the base of the Doomcrag. We need to open a path through the Shrouded Pass so we can assault Karnosis' stronghold.
I have found the notes of a mage named Mercano from Woodhearth in the depths of an Ayleid ruin where the Veiled Heritants were raising undead.
The time has come to confront Molag Bal and reclaim my soul.

I discovered the remains of a mage outside a cave in Shademist Moors. While there are no shortage of victims around here, the presence of the Mages Guild urges me to investigate what might have happened to the rest of them.
I found a dead adventurer in Barrow Trench. They entered the mine to collect rare ingredients for an alchemist in Woodhearth.
The Shade of Prince Naemon is spreading corruption across Greenshade. I must help Indaenir cleanse the corruption.

The Torog's Spite Bandits are dedicated to profit and vengeance from targeting families descended from those who sacked Orsinium. An Orc historian named Maaga wants to record the bandits' deeds but needs to know which Orc clan deserves credit.
Before losing Aranias' memories, the Wilderqueen told me that she knew about the Veiled Heritance plot to steal the Staff of Magnus. She suggested I go to the city of Woodhearth.
<<1>>, a priestess of Azura, has long suffered at the hands of Molag Bal. Her pain is so great it has torn a hole between <<2>> and <<3>>, an Ayleid ruin in <<4>>.
A Bosmer named Hartmin believes the Wilderking will soon disappear from Greenheart. He recalls there being blue flowers all over the area. These flowers are gone.
Verandis completed his research and discovered that his missing memories lead to an ancient ruin in the Lorkrata Hills. He needs my help to discover the secret hidden within the ruins.

The hamlet of Moira's Hope has met with disaster. Bloodfiends fill the streets, and the few survivors that remain are trying desperately to stay alive. I agreed to help Adusa-daro provide aid and find out who is behind this attack.
I met a Bosmer Adventurer named Gluineth locked in a cell in Troll's Toothpick. I've agreed to spring her from the cell and escort her out of the cave.

I found a Knight of St. Pelin in the Crypt of the Exiles who died while on an important quest. She sought to recover a sacred Redguard artifact, the Memory Stone of Makela Leki, and return it to a Redguard scholar.
Sai Sahan has recovered from his experiences in the the Halls of Torment and is ready to guide me to the Amulet of Kings. He hid the artifact in Sancre Tor, an ancient Imperial catacomb.
<<1>>'s citizens are killing one another in the streets. Dominion soldiers cordoned off the town, but are in dire need of assistance.
I accepted a Fighters Guild contract in Cyrodiil.
I accepted a Fighters Guild contract in Cyrodiil.
I accepted a Fighters Guild contract from Sebazi in Cyrodiil.
I accepted a Fighters Guild contract in Cyrodiil.
I accepted a Fighters Guild contract from Arkas at the Southern Morrowind gate.
I accepted a Fighters Guild contract in Cyrodiil.
I accepted the Fighters Guild contract Arkas offered.
I accepted a Fighters Guild contract from Arkas at the Southern Morrowind gate.
I accepted a Fighters Guild contract from Ikran at the Northern High Rock gate in Cyrodiil.
I accepted a Fighters Guild contract in Cyrodiil.
I accepted a Fighters Guild contract in Cyrodiil.
I accepted a Fighters Guild contract from Ikran at the Northern High Rock gate.
The princess of Evermore is being cared for in the Viridian Woods, but her future is uncertain.
<<1>>'s husband, a minstrel named Sorion, went missing after going on tour through <<2>>. I agreed to help track him down.
Now that Tainted-Heart is dead, Darien Gautier suggested I head north to help out that region of Rivenspire.
We've taken control of the Shrouded Pass and the way to the Doomcrag is open. The time has come to make our final assault and reach Montclair and  the cursed relic known as the Lightless Remnant.
The <<1>>, one of the legendary resting places of the Walking City of Falinesti, is buzzing with activity. It seems <<2>> has begun an excavation.
A novice from the Mages Guild named Gahgdar was duped by a witch into giving her a valuable book from the guildhall in Hallin's Stand. He asked me to help him get the book back.
Lady Clarisse Laurent is on the trail of the Emerald Chalice, a relic stolen from the Mages Guild by the exiled Nord mage, Malofar. She tracked him here to Breagha-Fin.
The Reachmen threat has been averted, but Evermore is still in danger, and Queen Arzhela needs my help.
On approaching <<1>>, I came upon <<2>>, a Khajiit in trouble with the local authorities.
The Llodos plague is ravaging the Deshaan countryside. I met someone from a town known as the Serk. He's on his way to warn people about the plague.
I found a strange glowing amulet on a corpse in the woods.
<<1>> has heard rumblings of discontent in <<2>>, the Aldmeri Dominion's capital. She wants me to travel ahead of her and assess the situation.
The information broker has information about the Montclair dealings.
Onsi's Breath was captured by Imperial soldiers who hold its inhabitants captive.
Reachmen attacked Northglen. They must be stopped before they can attack the city of  Evemore.
Imperials have been raiding Martyr's Crossing, and the Knights of Saint Pelin have wound up having to depend on the help of Baandari merchants for assistance.
A bloody conflict has erupted between the noble houses of Rivenspire and High King Emeric has asked me to go there on his authority and attempt to restore order.

Shornhelm, the largest city in Rivenspire, is a city divided. House Montclair has annexed part of the city. Darien Gautier suggested I go to Shornhelm and help Countess Tamrith and Baron Dorell deal with the situation.

I need to locate Verandis Ravenwatch and find out if he can tell me more about Baron Montclair and where he might be hiding. He may also know more about what set Montclair on this path of destruction.
<<1>> needs couriers to make deliveries around <<2>>.

I died, but that was only the beginning .nnI awoke in Oblivion. My body is intact, but my soul has been torn from my body. I must find a way out of this nightmare place to reclaim what was lost to me, or I will be damned for all eternity.
Scholar <<1>> and his guide, <<2>> became separated in the Sunken Road.

Imperial forces have taken control of Bangkorai Garrison, the strategic keep that divides northern and southern Bangkorai. King Emeric and the Lion Guard have come to aid Queen Arzhela and the Knights of Saint Pelin in reconquering the garrison.
I heard a rumor about a political group discussing Shornhelm's future. They meet at the old <<1>> regularly and are always looking for more recruits to their cause.
The ruins of the ancient Wood Elf village of Gil-Var-Delle is under the corrupting influence of Molag Bal. The Worm Cult is active here, and my help is needed to put an end to their schemes.
A group of vampire hunters has come to this area to cleanse it of its infestation, including a powerful vampire lord. They've asked for my assistance.
<<1>> is distraught. Her adorable pet, Puddles, ran away, and she's afraid that the little creature is lost.
The Vinedusk Rangers want me to help quash the remnants of the Blacksap Rebellion, the Wood Elf civil war that ended with the Dominion's formation.
Hallin's Stand is ready to take back their town from the Imperial's Seventh Legion.
<<1>> is writing a book about bloodfiends and needs help with the research.
I met <<1>> and <<2>> at their camp along the roadside. They're fleeing for their lives from their ransacked farmstead.
Now Aryette wants me to help her meet a real vampire.

If <<1>> is to prove herself worthy of leading the Aldmeri Dominion to glory, she must complete the ratification ceremony in <<c:2>> of <<3>>. Legends say it can reveal those worthy of becoming emperor  or empress.
Knights of Arkay search for holy relics to help combat the rising undead threat spreading throughout Rivenspire. So far, the knights have yet to return.

I met a somewhat drunk and totally bootless Breton named Parquier Gimbert outside of Northpoint. He said he lost a valuable mace while hunting for mudcrabs along the shore. He thinks that maybe a Hagraven was involved. Also, he has no shoes.

In ruined Klathzgar, I found a note from an Altmeri scholar investigating an ancient mystery. An Ayleid princess named Urenenya vanished centuries ago, and the scholar came here after learning of her connection to the Dwemer architect Klazthgar.
Adusa has further need of my help. She's learned of another plot, an assassin contracted by allies of House Montclair.
Adusa has discovered that the Montclairs have assembled a list of targets they have marked for elimination.
I returned to find Adusa and Castle Ravenwatch under attack. The list of targets puts Adusa right at the top.

Using the codebook I discovered, Adusa has determined that Montclair's nephew, Rohlbert, is behind the assassination plot. She believes that if we eliminate Rohlbert, we can end this part of the Montclair threat once and for all.
Teeba-Ja was a member of the Bitterhand Bandits, but when they became more violent, she decided to leave. She wants to start a new life in Shornhelm.

Constable Agazu says the mayor of Fell's Run fired her for no reason and appointed a new constable. She says all the townspeople are acting strange as well, but no one's talking. She wants me to help find out what's going on.
The information broker has information about the Montclair dealings.
The information broker has information about the Montclair dealings.
<<1>> has asked me to find her husband Ignobert, who went missing after a vampire attack.
Now that the threat to Rivenspire has been dealt with, there's still the matter of crowning a true ruler for the region.
Countess Tamrith has sent a priest to sanctify her dead soldiers at Camp Tamrith. Those particularly devoted to the Light of Arkay have a profound fear of turning into undead creatures.
Fallen Grotto is under the control of <<1>> and his Reachmen.
<<1>> has lost track of her husband and her dog. I've offered to help her look for both of them.
I found a glowing ring on a skeleton in an old camp. It is clearly magical but I can discern nothing else about it.
A refugee in Camp Tamrith is worried about her brother after he ran off to join bandits. She wants to know if he made it to <<1>> and whether he's ever going to return to her.
I met a man named Beryn in the woods, recovering from an epic drinking bout at his camp. He's worried because he fears his friend <<1>> has wandered into a nearby spider cave on a dare.
All is not well in <<1>>. The Khajiit lack an embassy, which is the cause of tensions in the capital city of the Aldmeri Dominion.

I discovered a research journal kept by an Orc named Grularz in Crestshade Mine. She was apparently studying the trolls until they decided to kill her. The journal referred to a brother named Gothurg in Shornhelm.
Adusa fears that Montclair agents still operate out of Shornhelm. She wants me to follow a courier in hopes the courier will lead me to the Montclair informer.
<<1>> is concerned for her friend <<2>>. He recently entered a cave full of deadly spiders and hasn't been seen since.
High King Emeric has arrived in Shornhelm. He needs to know about the danger from Karnosis and the Doomcrag.

Queen Maraya has asked a personal favor. She's heard disturbing rumors about some of her father's enemies returning, so she's asked me to go to Sentinel in the Alik'r Desert and ensure that both the kingdom and her father are safe.
<<1>> must complete the ratification ceremony if her allies are to accept her as leader of the Aldmeri Dominion. At the heart of the ceremony is <<c:2>>, an ancient Ayleid artifact.
Jowan and Mayla want to give their family a proper burial. They asked me to accompany them.
I was approached shortly after saving <<1>> from the Jackdaw attack. <<2>> approached me and revealed she works for the Wood Elf king. She said he needs the aid of impressive people such as myself.
I met an old scholar near the Ayleid ruins who came to power a crystal for his research, but found the ruins swarming with Worm Cultists.
I found a journal that belonged to a thief called Nedras the Sly. He apparently turned to crime in order to support his ailing sister in Northpoint.
I found a journal on the body of Klaandor Axe-Bearer. It details his transformation into a vampire. Seems like he was looking for someone to kill him.
I found a journal that belonged to a monk of the lunar faith named Yenadar. The journal mentions that he has a sister named <<1>> in S'ren-ja. I should return the journal to her.

Lleraya Montclair and her forces have taken control of Northpoint. They've sealed the gates and locked out the legitimate city guards. But Baron Dorell has a plan to liberate Northpoint. It just requires a small group willing to infiltrate the city.
After their defeat at Bangkorai Garrison, the Imperial forces retreated south, and King Emeric believes they will make their last stand here at the ancient temple known as the Hall of Heroes.

Imperial Magus-General Septima Tharn captured King Emeric and took him into the Chamber of Passage. It's apparently a gateway to the plane known as the Far Shores, where Redguards go in the afterlife.
A strange woman met me at the gates to the city. She may be a werewolf. She told me I am on my way to becoming one as well.
Redguard forces are massing inside an old Ayleid ruin, and the Dominion believes they've opened up a magical gateway from Alik'r to transport their troops into the heart of Grahtwood unopposed.
I was bitten by a vampire. I have the option of embracing the disease or receiving the cure.

I met Nicolene in the Dead Wolf Inn in Shornhelm. She and Captain Kaleen are here looking for one of King Fahara'jad's former spies, Naruk. Naruk has turned against the Daggerfall Covenant and is now inciting war, but Kaleen is missing.
I found a wanted poster offering a reward for the head of an Orc called Sgolag.
The Khajiit, <<1>>, has invited me to join a group of adventurers called the Undaunted.
A Daedra has taken over Nilata Ruins. Having possessed a farmer's wife, the Daedra is luring travelers into her lairlikely to their doom.
Something has been luring Imperial soldiers into the ruins. Many have been captured by the giant spiders lurking there.
We found a way to sneak into the sealed city of Northpointa tunnel used by smugglers and black marketeers. Now we need to head inside and find a way to free the city from Lleraya Montclair's grasp.
Before High King Emeric can appoint a new ruler to Shornhelm, the lost Crown of Shornhelm must be located.
While traveling in <<1>>, I found a shrine dedicated to the animals of the Valenwood. <<2>> said the shrine was created by <<3>>'s Briars, an elite group of hunters.
I met a priest of Y'ffre who seeks to heal the scarred ruin of Gil-Var-Delle by mixing blessed water into the falls that feed into the river of the vale. She asked me to help her in her task.
<<1>>'s Carnival came from the Summerset Isle to spread High Elf culture. Unfortunately, they've suffered numerous setbacks in performing for the Wood Elves of <<2>>.
High King Emeric wants to liberate southern Bangkorai from Imperial control. He believes the key to that is tracking down Imperial Magus General Septima Tharn.
<<1>> asked me to search the ruins for texts from other scholars who may have previously studied here.
Llotha asked me to help her unlock a lockbox by solving an old mystery about the Blacklight Raiders. The password to the lock is a combination of the Raiders' names and professions.
<<1>> of the Dragonstar Caravan Company asked for my assistance in fulfilling a contract for a mage in the Silaseli ruins.
target: <<1>> del Dragostar Caravan Company asked for my assistance in fulfilling a contract for a mage in the Silaseli ruins.

source: A scroll in the Tomb of the Blood Matron describes a ritual one must undergo to become a Scion of the Blood Matron.
I found a journal in a bandit camp. It detailed the murder of an Orc chieftan's two wives. It also mentioned a third wife named <<1>> who lives in a place called Barkbite.
For one to become a Scion of Lamae they must complete a ceremony. The details of that ceremony appear in a scroll within the Blood Matron's tomb.
<<1>>, an injured Orcish scout near <<2>>, seeks to rally others to his banner by acquiring <<3>> from the Seventh Legion <<4>> who devastated his Orcish brethren.
High King Emeric has arrived with the Lion Guard to help retake Bangkorai Garrison from the Imperial forces.
As <<1>> and a group of refugees traveled through southern Bangkorai, they were attacked by Imperials. Several of them lost priceless heirlooms.
The Wyress Freyda warned me away from Jackdaw Cove as dark forces are at work in northern Bangkorai.
A group of soldiers from Bangkorai Garrison lead by Sir Dubroc went out in search of the Reachman leader in Jackdaw Cove.
The garrison at Bangkorai Pass asked that a deliver a message to Evermore Castle.
The Imperials in Southern Bangkorai have set up some sort of dig around an ancient Redguard ruin called the Hall of Heroes.
Hircine has granted me the ability to induct new members in our pack. I can turn one person into a werewolf on every full moon.
Hircine, Daedric Prince of the Hunt, speaks to me through his statue. A werewolf has led me into Hircine's Hunting Ground. Here, one of Hircine's Packsworn may choose to make me part of their pact.
<<1>> has invited me to join a group of adventurers called the Undaunted.
Cadwell has turned the Harborage into his new homefor the time being, at any rate.
Soldiers from Evermore were defeated at Murcien's Hamlet by a Reachman attack.
I found a keg containing wine with magical properties.

With <<1>> deadagainand the new Silvenar revealed, <<2>> asked me to head to <<3>> in <<4>>. The Aldmeri Dominion needs to prepare for the wedding between the Green Lady and the newly-discovered Silvenar.
Something strange is happening inside Shroud Hearth Barrow that is frightening the villagers of Ivarstead.
I found an abandoned campfire at the entrance to <<1>>. I should figure out what happened to the campers.
The Dominion's lifeline to Malabal Tor is under siege. If I want to assist in the defense of <<1>>, I should speak with <<2>> near the gate to <<3>>.
A Pact soldier and his brother were captured by bandits after being caught spying. They were investigating the cult-like activity of the bandits.
I've found a scroll bearing marks from the Aldmeri Dominion. It details a series of unsolved murders in <<1>>.

The Ring of Daggers has tracked down a war criminal named Gerard Althen, who once served as King Ranser's spymaster. He's hiding somewhere in Sanguine Barrows and I've agreed to find him and bring him out.
<<1>> overheard Dominion soldiers brag of capturing <<Ac:2>>, where Argonian children in <<3>> are born.
I managed to drive the bandits from Fell's Run, but the bandit's leader, Leonce Gavendien, escaped with the stolen jewels.
Captain Thayer is having a difficult time recruiting new soldiers for the Shornhelm Guard. She asked me to help convince a man in the stocks to enlist.
Captain Thayer thinks her last prospect will pose the greatest challenge of all. His name is Julien Rissiel and he's reluctant to enlist because he's in love.
Captain Thayer has asked me to recruit a woman named Shuga into the Shornhelm Guard. Thayer suspects Shuga is actually a bandit who doesn't have much respect for the guard.
We put an end to Reezal-Jul and Lleraya. Now we need to deal with Baron Montclair. But to reach Montclair in his citadel atop the Doomcrag, we first need to find a way through the Shrouded Pass.
The guardian star sign of the Warrior has failed to appear to protect the mortal world from the Serpent. One of the Star-Gazers needs help uncovering what might be happening.
<<1>>, the betrothed of Arlie Edrald, has asked for my assistance in locating the Edrald family. He returned to prepare for his wedding to find that they had mysteriously vanished from their estate.

As part of the South Winds Festival, there is a mounted race being proctored by the priests of Kynareth. Participants of the derby will be rewarded with a blessing of good health if they can prove themselves worthy by beating a timed trial.
It looks as if Warwyrd Temple has come under attack. I should help defend it and save the priests that serve there.
A Herald has come with tales of a dire threat in the distant land of Craglorn.
With Honrich Tower secure, <<1>> asked that I seek out <<2>> in Taarengrav. The tomb holds one of Ysgramor's great companions and must be protected from the Worm Cult.
Lieutenant Slonn led a team of scholars to Pinepeak Caverns to awaken the spirit of Hakra, one of the five hundred companions, but the team hasn't returned.
<<1>> has been saved and Pinepeak is secure, but it seems Honrich Tower has been taken by the Worm Cult.
Covenant soldiers are massing within Softloam Cavern. It won't be long before they have the numbers to launch an attack on Kragenmoor and the rest of Stonefalls.
I found a soldier outside a spider cave in Stonefalls. She's suffering from a spider bite she received while trying to search the Hollow.
A High Elf named Caalorne was ambushed by a group of Argonians on the road to Kragenmoor. They stole a number of potions from him, and he wants them back.
A Pact Mage named Sees-Many-Paths is examining the wards at Tormented Spire. She wants word sent to her egg-sister, Walks-in-Ash, that they are unstable.
I met an Argonian named Onuja at Othrenis. He asked me to aid Davon's Watch in their battle against the Daggerfall Covenant.
I met a soldier at Ash Mountain who said the defense of Davon's Watch could use some help.
A soldier at Fort Virak told me the Pact military is focusing their efforts at the land coral maze known as Vivec's Antlers.
A Pact officer at Vivec's Antlers suggested I assist the generals at Ash Mountain.
I met an Ashlander hunter named Shuldrashi looking for her Argonian friend.
Captain Ronag at Shinji's Scarp asked me to deliver a dispatch to Clan Murtag soldiers near the at-Tura estate.
I ran into Blademaster Qariar in Northpoint's back alleys. He's hunting down the remaining vampires that were working with Lady Lleraya Montclair.
Sergeant Oorga is afraid she will die in her next battle and asked me to deliver an offering to Azura for her.
In the tangled paths of <<1>>, I found the bodies of a Lion Guard officer and his patrol.
A guardswoman in Skywatch has asked me to deliver a sealed message scroll to Vulkhel Guard for her.
I have accepted a mission to travel to Fort Warden and scout that stronghold for the Dominion.

The virulent Llodos plague spreads throughout Deshaan, and the town known as the Serk suffers under the effects of the ravaging disease. A group known as the Maulborn arrived to help, but some of the townsfolk are dubious about their true intentions.
A bored member of the Queen's entourage let me know Her Majesty plans to speak soon in the city of Vulkhel Guard.
The pages to the writer's book have been spread by the wind.
<<1>> was separated from her brother and sister.
Many people have been captured by the daedra.
A merchant in the Shrouded Vale reports seeing a village that has mysteriously and suddenly appeared in a nearby cave.
Fleeing undead to the north, a clan of Bosmer refugees wants to settle in Shadows Crawl, but stone men, known as Hollow, rose from the ground and attacked.
<<1>> was sent on a mission to close the portals beneath the Imperial City.
Many people have been injured during the daedra attacks.
Alchemist Nilyne Hlor doesn't trust the proprietary formula the Maulborn use to make their curative. She wants to examine a few bottles so she can determine how the elixir is made.

I met a strange Imperial who was being held captive by the Daggerfall Covenant. He believes he knows how to defeat the cursed army of Anka-Ra that has laid siege to Craglorn since the Celestials appeared.
Something about the way the book was placed in front of the statue makes it appear to be an offering.
A Hollow Guardian accosted me deep in the Valenwood. He asked me to go north and offer my assistance to the Bramblebreach clan.
I met Ibrula, a friend of the Star-Gazers who is trying to get into a ruined temple called the Seeker's Archive. She hopes to discover information inside that will help defeat the Celestials.
An aging Bosmer named Hartmin brought his dying husband to a grove near Greenheart where they share memories from their youth.

I found the ruins of a city called Shada's Tear in the middle of the Craglorn desert. A mercenary told me that some researchers from Belkarth went into the ruins, but that strange things started happening when they did.
In the depths of <<1>>, I found a <<2>> surrounded by bodies. One of them stirred when I took the urn.

Outside the school of blades called Rahni'Za, I encountered an intiate of the school who told me that the Sword-Disciples have been turned into thralls by a traitor. This betrayer now hides in the cavern at the end of the school's five trials.
People venturing into Hel Ra Citadel have mysteriously vanished, including a group of Undaunted led by Kailstig the Axe. I should enter the Citadel to find out what happened to them.
It seems that Prince Naemon has indeed returned from the dead and now leads an undead army that's pushed its way to the city gates of Marbruk.

The Ancient Keepers, sworn to imprison the spirit of High Kinlord Rilis, have taken to forming Daedric pacts. Keeper Cirion has asked for help in defeating the corrupting force of Rilis, but will require fighting the Keepers directly.
The priestess Kauzanabi-jo told me my next goal should be to help the Lunar Champions Rid-Thar spoke of. I should seek them out at the fort known as Grimwatch.
Shazah told me to travel to the city of Rawl'kha. There the next steps can be taken to name a new Mane.
A moon priest named Thalinfar told me that I was needed at Fort Grimwatch, to the north of Rawl'kha.

I've discovered the Aetherian Archive, an enigmatic tower that had previously been sealed. Mighty Mordra and her Undaunted had planned to climb the Archive, but her allies are missing. If I choose to, I could explore it and reach the top before them.
A shipment from Artisans Craftworks in Mournhold never made it to the merchant, Blivisi Beleth.

The Worm Cult has stolen the legendary axe Wuuthrad and plans to perform dark deeds with it. There are even rumors it was shattered, in which case we must find the shards of Wuuthrad wherever they may be.
Refugees outside of Elinhir told me that the city has been ransacked by mad mages. They sent me to Minerva Lauzon, who is gathering survivors in the sewers.

A giant object fell from the heavens when the Mage constellation disappeared. Sara Benele is examining the object, which she calls the "Mage's Staff." She believes the staff is unstable and needs my help to fix it.
Gasteau Chamrond knows how to escape the structure I've fallen into. He'll help me get out if I lend him my strength.
Hermaeus Mora asked me to bring him unique relics from across Craglorn in exchange for knowledge of the Celestials. Perhaps he'll be interested in this strange writing.
Nerien'eth the lich has returned to the Crypt of Hearts to find the ghosts he imprisoned there arrayed against him.
Hara has decided it's time to do something about the third guardian, the Thief. The Thief has been mysteriously absent except for when she appears to speak to me in private.
The Celestial Thief appeared to me and asked for my help discovering why the atronachs that were summoned to destroy the Dark Anchors turned against the mages of Craglorn.
<<1>> attempted to enter an Oblivion Gate with a group of Undaunted to save his wife, <<2>>. He failed. I'm to help him get her backif she still lives.
The magistrate of <<1>> falsely imprisoned a man named <<2>>.
Ann wants me to confuse and intimidate Magistrate Banu. She has a plan to rock him back on his heels.
Ann has asked me to make another run at Magistrate Banu. She thinks he'll be very off balance, thanks to our previous plots.

Ann's admitted to me this was all a plan to put her in power, to replace Banu as the Magistrate of Abah's Landing. She's made me a part of her crew, a trusted advisor. All that's left is the last step.

Danni wants to recruit the last member for the big operation she's planning,. That person is Gwenneth, a master thief. Unfortunately, Gwenneth is locked away in a high security prison known as Xarxes' Rebuke.
In order to get into the Whispered Ball, we need invitations. Danni asked me to help her break into the houses of various Twilight Lodge members and steal invitations from them.

In order to steal the skeleton key from the Vault of Shadows, the crew needs to find a way to get to the vault. Danni has a plan. Together with Nick and Gwenneth, I am to steal a ship worthy enough to transport the crew to the vault.
I encountered a Star-Gazer who told me that two High Elf women inside the Crossroad Tavern claim to be aspects of the Celestial Mage. I should talk to them and investigate their claims.
I've been asked to prove my worth as a thief for the Thieves Guild.
Danni has asked me to help her on a mission in the Gray Barrows.

Safa al-Satakalaam, a priest of Satakal, is at odds with the Scaled Court. Three of her most powerful acolytes have deserted her to worship the Celestial Serpent. She wants me to punish these traitors and deny their power to the Scaled Court.
The Black Horse Couriers have set up riding challenges across Tamriel. I should find and complete them.
The Black Horse Couriers have set up riding challenges across Tamriel. I should find and complete them.
The Black Horse Couriers have set up riding challenges across Tamriel. I should find and complete them.
The Black Horse Couriers have set up riding challenges across Tamriel. I should find and complete them.
The Black Horse Couriers have set up riding challenges across Tamriel. I should find and complete them.
The Black Horse Couriers have set up riding challenges across Tamriel. I should find and complete them.
The Black Horse Couriers have set up riding challenges across Tamriel. I should find and complete them.
The Black Horse Couriers have set up riding challenges across Tamriel. I should find and complete them.
The Black Horse Couriers have set up riding challenges across Tamriel. I should find and complete them.
The Black Horse Couriers have set up riding challenges across Tamriel. I should find and complete them.
The Black Horse Couriers have set up riding challenges across Tamriel. I should find and complete them.
The Black Horse Couriers have set up riding challenges across Tamriel. I should find and complete them.
The Black Horse Couriers have set up riding challenges across Tamriel. I should find and complete them.
The Black Horse Couriers have set up riding challenges across Tamriel. I should find and complete them.
The Black Horse Couriers have set up riding challenges across Tamriel. I should find and complete them.
An Imperial squad was decimated by the Daedra. One of the survivors asked me to see if Eulintus is still alive in the Arena District.
The Rat told of the Bloodworks, an underground prison and torture chamber. Sounds like he spent some time in there. Perhaps I can save others from his fate.
A small band of Hircine cultists have gathered in Craglorn. They've come to hunt the dangerous beasts unleashed by the Scaled Court. They're obnoxious and need to be taught a lesson.
Daedra are raiding the Nobles District and capturing people to be used as fodder in the arena. A dying arena fighter named Dyus Previa asked me to stop them.

Iron Orcs, who usually don't take prisoners, have started abducting travelers near the Valley of Scars. I encountered a caravan master who survived an attack, though a number of his guards were dragged off by the Orcs.

I met an Iron Orc shaman who had been banished by a younger rival. What's more, this rival, named Agganor, seems to be responsible for the Iron Orc and Scaled Court alliance. The old shaman wants me to avenge him.
An Imperial priestess told me of unholy acts being committed in the Temple District. Priestess Faltonia should know more.
The Rat says the Daedra have captured many citizens and taken them to the arena to be slaughtered.
The Listener has named me the Wrath of Sithis and expects me to enforce the Five Tenets.
The Listener has a high profile mission for me: Jarl Kalgar in Greataxe Hold.
The Rat hates the Flesh Colossi in the Arena District.

The Rat says that most of the arena fighters are dead because the Daedra make them fight in the arena repeatedly without giving them any healing between bouts. The Rat gave me poultices to heal the ones who remain.
I have been sent by the Keeper to the Free Legion's Redoubt, under orders to kill the Captain of the mercenaries, by request of one Marganus.

The scholar Nendirume warned me that the Scaled Court has taken over the ruined city of Skyreach. She believes they're searching Skyreach Hold for more of the nirncrux element, which they refer to as "the blood of Nirn."

I've discovered the Aetherian Archive, an enigmatic tower that had previously been sealed. Mighty Mordra and her Undaunted had planned to climb the Archive, but her allies are missing. If I choose to, I could explore it and reach the top before them.

The Listener has given me a contract, one he hopes will be an opportunity to prove myself without interference from the current Dark Brotherhood politics.nnI am to kill Adreso Relvi at his home in Morrowind, a plantation named for the Zachak Hills.
General Nedras wants a report on conditions in the City's Arboretum District. I need to find Captain Thorasa, if I can, and tell her to send the general a report.

A woman claiming to be the leader of the Scaled Court requested my help. This Regent Cassipia wants me to help her stop the Scaled Court's process for creating a new type of creature for the Serpent's growing armythe mantikora.
Famius and Annia Sisenna fled home and friends when the Daedra took over the City. Famius asked me to check on Maximinus in the Market District.
Captain Ocella asked me to travel to the Nobles District and find her brother there.
A refugee named Venetia hates the merchant Maximinus in the Market District and hopes that he's dead.
The Dark Brotherhood would like to have me join their ranks. They've asked me to try out for the assassin's guild. If I pass their tests, then I can join the mysterious death cult.
General Aklash wants a report on conditions in the City's Arboretum District. I need to find Captain Thorasa, if I can, and tell her to send the general a report.
Councilor Itinia of the Imperial City's Elder Council is down in the sewers, but she's worried about the Imperial citizens who remain up in the city.
The Imperial noble Severianus hopes to recover his losses by collecting a debt from a merchant named Maximinus in the Market District.
Sergeant Buca asked me to check on conditions in the City's Arboretum District and find Captain Thorasa, if I can.

A Wood Elf named Little Leaf claims she's on a mission to stop the Iron Orcs from building a troll army. She tried to appeal to the Orc leaders, but diplomacy didn't work. Now she wants me to come along and try a more forceful approach.
Captain Brocchus asked me to travel to the Nobles District to find Sergeant Ocella and his squad.
The Night Mother has asked a task of me. I need to kill the Listener.
The Keeper has an intriguing contract that he feels I am just right for.
<<1>> asked me to search for weapon caches the Fighters Guild hid around the district.
Hall Steward Kerennia has asked me to collect the heads of Clannfear from around the Market District.
According to Steward Kerennia the Worm Cult mages in the Market District have started using "dreadshards" to enhance the power of their spells.
Regulinus Bucco's "medicine" has gone missing, somewhere in the Market District. He's desperate to find it.
Imperial citizens are being held around the Temple District. They'll be sacrificed to Molag Bal if not rescued.
Grand Warlord Sorcalin has authorized a reward for any Dominion soldier who slays 20 enemy Templars.
Grand Warlord Dortene has authorized a reward for any Covenant soldier who slays 20 enemy Templars.
Grand Warlord Zimmeron has authorized a reward for any Pact soldier who slays 20 enemy Templars.
Statues of the Eight Divines have been thrown down, their pieces scattered throughout the Temple District. <<1>> asked me to collect any fragments I find.
Shrines to Molag Bal have been set up in the Temple District. Valerianus Lentinus has asked me to destroy some of them using a relic he salvaged from the temple.
Daedra have returned to the Temple of the Divines and resumed conducting a dangerous summoning ritual. Priestess Simplicia asked me to disrupt the ritual once again.
Grand Warlord Sorcalin has authorized a reward for any Dominion soldier who slays 20 enemy Dragonknights.
Grand Warlord Dortene has authorized a reward for any Covenant soldier who slays 20 enemy Dragonknights.
Grand Warlord Zimmeron has authorized a reward for any Pact soldier who slays 20 enemy Dragonknights.
Grand Warlord Sorcalin has authorized a reward for any Dominion soldier who slays 20 enemy Nightblades.
Grand Warlord Dortene has authorized a reward for any Covenant soldier who slays 20 enemy Nightblades.
Grand Warlord Zimmeron has authorized a reward for any Pact soldier who slays 20 enemy Nightblades.
Grand Warlord Sorcalin has authorized a reward for any Dominion soldier who slays 20 enemy Sorcerers.
Grand Warlord Dortene has authorized a reward for any Covenant soldier who slays 20 enemy Sorcerers.
Grand Warlord Zimmeron has authorized a reward for any Pact soldier who slays 20 enemy Sorcerers.
Defend this keep to the last warrior standing! Kill any who dare assault Fort Warden!

A devout knight of the Divines discovered that the dead have awakened in the depths of Skyreach Catacombs. If the legend of Virmaril is true, then a powerful Elven necromancer could be the source of the trouble.
I met Titus Valerius in Belkarth. He was hoping to find Kelmen to assist him and the Thief with a ritual to locate a magical disturbance near Skyreach, but the mage is nowhere to be found.

Outside the ancient ruins of Skyreach Pinnacle, I met a member of the Scaled Court. He told me that the Court accidentally released creatures from magical wards the Nedes set up long ago. He plans to reestablish the wards, but he needs help.

An eccentric High Elf named Elanwen is desperately seeking a way to stabilize red brittlea rare but dangerous element also known as nirncrux. The Scaled Court has discovered the secret of the element and Elanwen is anxious to steal it from them.

Regent Cassipia has asked me to find her seneschal, Little Leaf, somewhere along the road through the northeast passage. She wants me to offer my aid to Little Leaf and help her foil another one of the Scaled Court's plans.
Maj al-Ragath of the Undaunted has challenged me to delve the Banished Cells beneath Auridon.
Little Leaf has asked me to find her friend, Regent Cassipia, in Dragonstar. She claims that the two of them are working from the inside to stop the Scaled Court.
The Undaunted warrior Glirion the Redbeard has challenged me to delve the Veteran Banished Cells beneath Auridon.
Maj al-Ragath of the Undaunted has challenged me to explore the Fungal Grotto beneath Stonefalls.
The Undaunted warrior Glirion the Redbeard has challenged me to explore Veteran Fungal Grotto in the caverns beneath Stonefalls.
If I can prove I know my way around a forge, <<1>> will certify me as a blacksmith.
Sergeant Shaghila says the Daedra have reinforcements coming from Coldharbour through portals that lead directly into the sewers.
Molag Bal's forces have set up portals to Coldharbour in the Imperial sewers. Daedric horrors issue from them continuously.
Molag Bal's forces have set up portals to Coldharbour in the Imperial sewers. Daedric horrors issue from them continuously.
General Nedras says the Dominion's first priority in the Imperial City is destroying the dark anchors in the upper city. Before we can do that, though, we need to figure out how to destroy them.
<<1>> believes the Worm Cult has been corrupting the already foul waters of the City sewers.
General Aklash says our priority in the Imperial City is destroying the Dark Anchors and estabishing Covenant control in strategic city districts.

The Celestial Warrior is worried about his champion, Titus Valerius. Lost in time, Titus' memory has begun to break apart. He no longer remembers who he is or his connection to the Warrior. Without his memory, the Warrior can't send him home.
Master crafters are offering free training and certification in their professions. Crafting certification will allow me to fulfill crafting writs.
Maj al-Ragath of the Undaunted has challenged me to explore the cavern called Spindleclutch beneath Glenumbra.
Glirion the Redbeard has challenged me to explore the cavern called Veternan Spindleclutch beneath Glenumbra.
Maj al-Ragath of the Undaunted has challenged me to explore the kwama mine called Darkshade Caverns, which lies beneath Deshaan.
Glirion the Redbeard has challenged me to explore the kwama mines of Veteran Darkshade Caverns beneath Deshaan.
Maj al-Ragath of the Undaunted has challenged me to explore the ancient complex beneath Elden Root, the Elden Hollow, in the center of Grahtwood.
Glirion the Redbeard has challenged me to explore the ruins beneath Grahtwood, the Veteran Elden Hollow.
Maj al-Ragath of the Undaunted has challenged me to explore the complex of sewers beneath Wayrest, dead center in the region called Stormhaven.
Sergeant Shaghila says Legion Zero saboteurs are killing our soldiers by rigging tunnels in the upper sewers to collapse.
<<1>> claims that Legion Zero soldiers allied with the Daedra are sabotaging parts of the upper sewer tunnels.
<<1>> says that Legion Zero saboteurs are rigging tunnels in the upper sewer to collapse on our patrols.
Glirion the Redbeard has challenged me to explore the tunnels and caverns that lie beneath Wayrest, the Veteran Wayrest Sewers.
Maj al-Ragath of the Undaunted has challenged me to explore the ruined halls of the Crypt of Hearts. It lies beneath the stones of Rivenspire, a former school for might and magic.
Glirion the Redbeard has challenged me to explore the ruins and hallways of Veteran Crypt of Hearts, beneath Rivenspire.
Sergeant Shaghila asked me to look for missing scouts in the Nobles Plaza Sewers.
<<1>> asked me to look for some scouts who have gone missing.
<<1>> asked me to look for some scouts who have gone missing in the Sewer Waterworks.
